2C%20spoke%20about%20the%20theory%20in%20a%20minute-and-a-half-long%20video%20on%20TikTok%20and%20explained%20the%20fascination%20with%20Doritos%20and%20other%20chips%2C%20as%20per%20a%20report%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnypost.com%2F2024%2F02%2F17%2Flifestyle%2Fthe-dorito-theory-explained-and-how-it-could-help-you-break-an-addiction-to-social-media%2F%3Futm_source%3Dwhatsapp_sitebuttons%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20She%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20eat%20a%20Dorito%20and%20finish%20your%20bite%2C%20you're%20not%20fully%20satisfied%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20the%20same%20as%20eating%20a%20steak%20or%20eating%20a%20really%20satiating%20food%20that's%20high%20in%20protein%20where%20after%20your%20bite%2C%20you%20really%20feel%20sort%20of%20that%20fullness%20and%20that%20warmth%20of%20satisfaction.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20continued%3A%20%26quot%3BEating%20potato%20chips%20is%20addictive%20because%20the%20peak%20of%20experience%20is%20kind%20of%20when%20you're%20tasting%20it%2C%20and%20not%20after.%26quot%3B%20It%20essentially%20means%20that%20the%20experiences%20that%20do%20not%20give%20an%20individual%20true%20satisfaction%20are%20maximally%20addictive.%20This%20can%20be%20applied%20to%20other%20areas%20of%20life%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20scrolling%20on%20social%20media%20applications%20or%20even%20things%20like%20excessive%20drinking%20or%20toxic%20relationships%20can%20be%20equally%20disappointing.%20She%20said%20giving%20a%20name%20to%20the%20problem%20allows%20her%20to%20more%20easily%20resist%20those%20compulsive%20behaviours.%20Social%20media%20use%20has%20frequently%20been%20compared%20to%20drug%20addiction%2C%20particularly%20when%20screen%20time%20negatively%20impacts%20everyday%20functioning%2C%20academic%20or%20professional%20performance%2C%20or%20even%20mental%20health%2C%20as%20per%20in%20the%20outlet.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20only%20this%20but%20spending%20too%20much%20time%20on%20social%20media%20applications%20has%20been%20connected%20to%20depression%20and%20negative%20body%20image.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20seen%20an%20increase%20in%20anxiety%2C%20depression%2C%20and%20addiction%2C%20including%20digital%20addiction%2C%20among%20our%20youth%20since%20the%20start%20of%20COVID%2C%26quot%3B%20Mental%20health%20expert%20Dr.%20Gregory%20Jantz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlice%20Shepard%2C%20clinical%20psychologist%20and%20the%20owner%20of%20Mirielle%20Therapy%20Practice%20told%20%3Cem%3EUSA%20Today%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BBad%20habits%20can%20be%20related%20to%20unfulfilling%20romantic%20relationships%2C%20friendships%20we%20should%20have%20let%20go%20of%20years%20ago%2C%20jobs%20that%20no%20longer%20work%20for%20us.%20These%20require%20thoughtful%20decisions%20and%20actions.%20Perhaps%20we%20want%20to%20return%20to%20the%20beginning%20when%20these%20situations%20felt%20good.%20Unfortunately%2C%20drugs%2C%20alcohol%20and%20excessive%20consumption%20of%20yummy%20but%20nutritionally%20empty%20foods%20won't%20solve%20our%20problems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20theory%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20way%20to%20identify%20one's%20problem%20areas.%20According%20to%20Rita%20McNamara%2C%20a%20lecturer%20in%20cross-cultural%20psychology%20at%20Victoria%20University%20of%20Wellington%2C%20%26quot%3BOur%20worst%20habits%20have%20that%20addictive%20drive%20to%20them.%20The%20difference%20between%20this%20kind%20of%20pleasure%20that%20drives%20addiction%20and%20true%20satisfaction%20is%20that%20addiction%20comes%20from%20chasing%20the%20peak%20experience%2C%20while%20satisfaction%20is%20a%20quiet%20beast.%20You%20actually%20can't%20chase%20satisfaction%2C%20it%20just%20arises.%20So%20there's%20nothing%20to%20get%20addicted%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708275720000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-02%2F78k0c2j_doritos_625x300_18_February_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.