I%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fgazas-second-largest-hospital-faces-closure-leaving-patients-in-distress%2Farticleshow%2F107795720.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fgazas-second-largest-hospital-faces-closure-leaving-patients-in-distress%2Famp_articleshow%2F107795720.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fgazas-second-largest-hospital-faces-closure-leaving-patients-in-distress%2Famp_articleshow%2F107795720.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22From%20Politics%20to%20Movies%20and%20Back%20Again%3A%20The%20Story%20of%20Urdu%20Magazine%20'Din%20Dunia'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18154308%2FDin-Dunia.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Asif%20Fehmi%20is%20an%20editor%20without%20a%20job.%20His%20monthly%20Urdu%20magazine%2C%20%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20ceased%20to%20publish%20during%20the%20pandemic%20due%20to%20financial%20difficulties.%20The%20magazine%20has%20a%20long%20history%20of%20surviving%20and%20documenting%20the%20crises%20that%20the%20nation%20went%20through.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20the%20legacy%20that%20was%20lost%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20remarks%20one%20winter%20morning%20while%20sipping%20coffee%20and%20sitting%20at%20his%20makeshift%20office%20in%20one%20of%20the%20by-lanes%20of%20Old%20Delhi.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20started%20in%20the%20crisis%20and%20ended%20in%20the%20crisis%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20laments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20a%20historical%20magazine%20that%20first%20came%20out%20in%201925%2C%20before%20India%20became%20independent.%20It%20was%20started%20by%20Khawaja%20Hassan%20Nizami%2C%20a%20poet%20and%20historian%20who%20was%20actively%20involved%20in%20politics%20and%20had%20a%20rivalry%20with%20Diwan%20Singh%20Maftoon%2C%20another%20famous%20Urdu%20journalist%2C%20over%20the%20princely%20states%20in%20the%20British%20Raj.%20It%E2%80%99s%20coming%20into%20being%20was%20political%2C%20as%20it%20was%20started%20to%20support%20the%20political%20stance%20of%20Khawaja%20Hassan%20Nizami.%20After%20the%20rivalry%20ended%2C%20Nizami%20handed%20over%20the%20magazine%20to%20Mufti%20Shoukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%2C%20Asif%20Fehmi%E2%80%99s%20father%2C%20who%20then%20became%20the%20editor%20and%20managed%20the%20magazine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20Mufti%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%20took%20over%20as%20editor%20of%20the%20magazine%2C%20its%20content%20was%20filled%20with%20political%20articles.%20Against%20the%20odds%2C%20to%20have%20advertisements%20and%20business%2C%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%20started%20the%20film%20section%20in%20the%20magazine%20that%20covered%20film%20controversies%2C%20gossip%20about%20the%20Hindi%20film%20industry%20and%20offered%20criticism%20on%20movies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsif%20Fehmi%20remembers%20his%20father%20telling%20him%20that%20then-famous%20Jaddanbai%20Hussain%2C%20singer%2C%20dancer%2C%20and%20actress%20of%20Indian%20cinema%2C%20and%20famous%20actress%20Saira%20Banu%2C%20visited%20the%3Cem%3E%20Din%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%20office.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20were%20various%20Hindi%20film%20personalities%20who%20visited%20the%20%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%20office%2C%E2%80%9D%20Asif%20Fehmi%20says%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20was%20a%20fear%20in%20the%20Hindi%20film%20industry%20of%20negative%20coverage%20by%20the%20magazine.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%201935%20to%201947%2C%20films%20dominated%20the%20magazine.%20As%20the%20subcontinent%20was%20partitioned%20in%201947%2C%20the%20magazine%20shut%20down%20for%20the%20first%20time%20%E2%80%9Cbecause%20of%20the%20circumstances%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%9D.%20Mufti%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%20migrated%20to%20Lahore%20and%20opened%20a%20shop%20in%20Anarkali%20Bazaar.%20Right%20after%20migrating%20to%20the%20other%20side%2C%20he%20felt%20it%20was%20not%20the%20right%20country%20for%20him%20and%20decided%20to%20return%20to%20Delhi.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20chose%20Delhi%20over%20Lahore%2C%E2%80%9D%20Asif%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%201947%2C%20as%20the%20subcontinent%20was%20partitioned%20and%20the%20socio-political%20scenario%20of%20the%20country%20changed%2C%20%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%20came%20out%20with%20a%20new%20version.%20The%20film%20section%2C%20for%20which%20the%20magazine%20was%20known%20previously%2C%20was%20skipped.%20Instead%2C%20Islamic%20history%2C%20Tafseer-e-Quran%20and%20historic%20incidents%20of%20the%20Islamic%20world%20found%20their%20way%20into%20the%20magazine.%20Now%20the%20magazine%E2%80%99s%20focus%20shifted%20to%20historical%2C%20political%20and%20mainly%20religious%20events%20in%20the%20country%20and%20the%20world.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20the%20societal%20need%20of%20the%20time%20to%20include%20Islamic%20history%20and%20carry%20Tafseer-e-Quran%20in%20parts%2C%E2%80%9D%20Asif%20Fehmi%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20famous%20%E2%80%98Raftar-e-Zamana%E2%80%99%20column%20for%20the%20editorial%20largely%20focused%20on%20violence%20against%20minorities%20after%201947.%20Mufti%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%20used%20his%20pen%20as%20a%20tool%20for%20speaking%20truth%20to%20power.%20His%20editorials%20were%20incisively%20political%2C%20busting%20myths%20that%20were%20used%20to%20target%20minorities%20and%20create%20an%20atmosphere%20of%20hostility.%20These%20editorials%20are%20preserved%20by%20his%20son%20Asif%20Fehmi%20in%20his%20book%20%3Cem%3EMufti%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%2C%20Hayaat%20va%20Khidmaat%3C%2Fem%3E%20(%3Cem%3EMufti%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%2C%20Life%20and%20Contributions%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20which%20he%20dedicated%20to%20his%20father.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201959%2C%20in%20the%20January%20issue%20of%20the%20magazine%2C%20the%20editorial%20focused%20on%20Bombay%E2%80%99s%20Dhulia%20riots.%20Mufti%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%20condemned%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20violence%E2%80%9D%20and%20wrote%20against%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgovernment%E2%80%99s%20inability%20to%20stop%20the%20riots%20and%20not%20being%20able%20to%20create%20a%20peaceful%20environment%20for%20the%20minorities%20to%20exist%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20editorial%2C%20in%20the%20May%20issue%20of%20the%20magazine%2C%20he%20wrote%20that%20%E2%80%9Criots%20are%20prevalent%20in%20the%20country%20every%20now%20and%20then%20after%201947.%20It%20has%20become%20our%20daily%20reality.%E2%80%9D%20He%20even%20targeted%20newspapers%20like%20%3Cem%3EPratap%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20propagating%20hate%20against%20Muslims.%20In%20the%20August%20editorial%20of%20the%20magazine%2C%20he%20went%20on%20to%20write%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccommunal%20disharmony%20is%20not%20the%20issue%20of%20Muslims%20but%20of%20unity%2C%20of%20democracy%2C%20of%20nationhood%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CNot%20a%20month%20passes%20without%20riots%20happening%20in%20India.%20Secularism%20has%20failed%3B%20it%20has%20been%20shredded%20to%20pieces%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20editorial%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201963%20editorial%20of%20%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Shaukat%20Fehmi%20accused%20%3Cem%3EAmrit%20Bazaar%20Patrika%2C%20Anand%20Bazaar%20Patrika%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%20%3Cem%3EPratap%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20%E2%80%9Cinciting%20communal%20disharmony%20and%20peddling%20hate%20against%20Muslims%E2%80%9D.%20He%20went%20on%20to%20suggest%20that%20%E2%80%9Cif%20we%20need%20to%20fight%20against%20communalism%2C%20all%20minorities%20have%20to%20unite.%20Jan%20Sangh%20is%20the%20enemy%20of%20each%20minority%20in%20India.%20India%20will%20be%20destroyed%20by%20communalism.%20All%20parties%20need%20to%20unite%20to%20fight%20against%20Jan%20Sangh.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18154421%2FDD.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18154421%2FDD.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18154421%2FDD-300x96.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18154421%2FDD-1024x328.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697712%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22384%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOld%20covers%20of%20%E2%80%98Din%20Dunia%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20of%20his%20editorials%2C%20Shaukat%20Fehmi%20also%20accused%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20of%20%E2%80%9Ccreating%20an%20atmosphere%20of%20fear%20in%20the%20country%20for%20minorities%E2%80%9D%20and%20prophesied%20that%20in%20the%20near%20future%20they%20will%20work%20for%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccreation%20of%20Hindu%20Rashtra%20and%20will%20rename%20the%20historical%20buildings%20ascribed%20to%20Muslims%2C%20an%20example%20being%20Taj%20Mahal%E2%80%9D.%20He%20also%20slammed%20the%20Congress%20for%20not%20providing%20%E2%80%9CMuslims%20and%20other%20minorities%20the%20space%20for%20equity%20in%20the%20social%2C%20political%2C%20and%20economic%20spectrum%2C%20which%20thus%20helps%20the%20RSS%20in%20further%20propagating%20their%20mission%20of%20Hindu%20India%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20said%20that%20with%20the%20partition%20of%20the%20subcontinent%2C%20the%20Urdu%20language%20was%20also%20partitioned.%20The%20decline%20in%20the%20readership%20of%20Urdu%20has%20always%20been%20a%20focus%20for%3Cem%3E%20Din%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Shaukat%20Fehmi%2C%20in%20one%20of%20his%20editorials%20that%20focused%20on%20the%20Urdu%20language%2C%20called%20it%20%E2%80%9CCinderella%E2%80%9D%20because%20%E2%80%9Cit%20awaits%20the%20magic%20touch%20that%20can%20free%20it%20from%20its%20minority%20status%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20condemned%20the%201986%20Education%20Policy%2C%20in%20which%20%E2%80%9Cno%20attention%20was%20paid%20to%20Urdu%E2%80%9D.%20He%20writes%20in%20one%20of%20his%20editorials%20that%20%E2%80%9CUrdu%20was%20born%20here%3B%20it%20grew%20up%20here.%20More%20than%20the%20Muslims%2C%20the%20Hindus%20also%20grew%20up%20reading%20and%20writing%20in%20this%20language.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98Raftar-e-Zamana%E2%80%99%20was%20a%20much-awaited%20column%20that%20attracted%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%20from%20readers.%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20used%20to%20wait%20for%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20Asif%20Fehmi%20says.%20It%20dealt%20with%20the%20most%20sensitive%20and%20critical%20issues%20of%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20is%20currently%20under%20governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%2C%20Shaukat%20Fehmi%20long%20ago%20criticised%20governor%E2%80%99s%20rule%20in%20one%20of%20his%20editorials%20written%20in%20February%201990%2C%20when%20the%20state%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%20was%20under%20the%20rule%20of%20Governor%20Jagmohan.%20He%20mentioned%20in%20the%20editorial%20that%20%E2%80%9Cit%E2%80%99s%20the%20only%20unlucky%20state%20of%20India%20that%20sinks%20into%20Governor%20Raj%20every%20now%20and%20then%E2%80%9D.%20While%20praising%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccommunal%20harmony%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20erstwhile%20state%20of%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20he%20also%20wrote%20that%20%E2%80%9Cparadise%20on%20earth%20has%20been%20turned%20into%20hell%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cnobody%20is%20serious%20enough%20to%20solve%20this%20issue%E2%80%9D.%20He%20also%20termed%20it%20the%20%E2%80%9Cmain%20cause%20of%20conflict%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20year%201992%2C%20when%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20was%20demolished%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Ayodhya%2C%20%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%20took%20a%20strong%20stance.%20It%E2%80%99s%20editorial%20condemned%20the%20%E2%80%9CRSS%2C%20VHP%2C%20and%20Rath%20Yatra%E2%80%9D%20and%20predicted%20that%20it%20would%20lead%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Cworse%20situation%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CWhatever%20is%20happening%20in%20Ayodhya%20is%20not%20sudden.%20It%20is%20well-planned%E2%80%A6%5Band%20the%5D%20mandate%20is%20given%20to%20them%20by%20people%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20editorial%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Asif%20Fehmi%2C%20journalism%20happened%20abruptly.%20Mufti%20Shaukat%20Ali%20Fehmi%2C%20who%20had%20managed%20and%20edited%20the%20magazine%2C%20died%20in%201993%20after%20being%20ill%20for%20two%20years.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20was%20no%20one%20to%20look%20after%20the%20magazine.%20It%20was%20our%20legacy.%20We%20were%20associated%20with%20the%20magazine.%20We%20are%20still%20known%20as%20%E2%80%98Din%20Dunia-wale%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20Asif%20Fehmi%20says%2C%20as%20he%20remembers%20the%20time%20when%20he%20took%20over%20as%20editor%20of%20the%20magazine.%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20my%20father%20died%2C%20I%20was%20already%20running%20the%20magazine.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManaging%20the%20magazine%20was%20a%20tough%20job%20for%20young%20Asif%20Fehmi.%20His%20education%20was%20English-based%2C%20and%20he%20had%20only%20read%20Urdu%20as%20a%20subsidiary%20subject%20in%20college.%20Before%20that%2C%20Asif%20was%20involved%20in%20clerical%20work%20for%20the%20magazine%20while%20his%20father%20was%20alive%20and%20was%20given%20a%20stipend%20for%20it.%20That%20is%20how%20Asif%20entered%20the%20legacy%20that%20his%20father%20had%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPublishing%20a%20magazine%20is%20a%20job%20where%20you%20require%20teamwork.%20But%20here%20it%20was%20done%20single-handedly%20by%20me.%20I%20managed%20the%20whole%20thing%3A%20proofreading%2C%20content%20gathering%20and%20publishing%2C%E2%80%9D%20Asif%20Fehmi%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20two%20people%20were%20working%20under%20him%20%E2%80%93%20one%20managing%20the%20clerical%20work%20and%20the%20other%20helping%20with%20the%20editorial%20work.%20The%20magazine%20was%20supported%20by%20the%20publication%20of%20books%20alongside%20it.%20Financial%20viability%20was%20one%20of%20the%20major%20reasons%20that%20hindered%20the%20publication%20of%20the%20magazine%20and%20later%20shut%20it%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Asif%20Fehmi%20pursued%20the%20struggle%20of%20keeping%20the%20%E2%80%9Clegacy%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20family%20alive%2C%20which%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cservice%20to%20society%2C%E2%80%9D%20up%20until%20the%20pandemic%20hit%20the%20country%20in%202020.%20During%20the%20pandemic%2C%20the%20offices%20of%20%3Cem%3EDin%20Dunia%3C%2Fem%3E%20were%20seized%20by%20the%20Municipal%20Corporation.%20%E2%80%9CThey%20don%E2%80%99t%20permit%20any%20industrial%20work%20in%20the%20walled%20city%2C%20not%20even%20printing%20presses%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%2C%20over%20the%20years%2C%20the%20readership%20of%20Urdu%20has%20declined%20massively.%20Digitisation%20has%20affected%20the%20readership%20of%20Urdu%20magazines%20and%20newspapers.%20%E2%80%9CTimes%20have%20changed.%20Urdu%20lovers%20don%E2%80%99t%20prefer%20to%20read%20Urdu%20newspapers.%20There%20was%20a%20time%20when%20people%E2%80%99s%20only%20source%20of%20information%20was%20newspapers%20and%20magazines.%20Nowadays%2C%20it%20is%20the%20internet%20and%20social%20media%2C%E2%80%9D%20Asif%20Fehmi%20explains.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20four%20years%20later%2C%20Asif%20Fehmi%20has%20only%20memories%20of%20his%20lost%20legacy.%20He%20has%20an%20archive%20that%20has%20the%20print%20issues%20of%20the%20magazine%20collected%20in%20a%20large%20file.%20He%20misses%20being%20in%20the%20office.%20His%20days%20are%20spent%20only%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20reviving%20the%20magazine.%20Asif%20Fehmi%20aims%20to%20bring%20the%20magazine%20back%20in%20digital%20form%20and%20in%20print%20quarterly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20not%20very%20sure%20about%20the%20digitisation%20of%20the%20magazine%2C%20but%20I%20am%20positive%20about%20it.%20Will%20I%20be%20able%20to%20do%20it%3F%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know.%20There%20is%20uncertainty.%20And%20I%20lack%20experience%20in%20the%20digital%20field%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbut%20it%20will%20always%20have%20a%20place%20in%20my%20memory.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EMir%20Umar%20is%20an%20independent%20journalist%20based%20in%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708251373000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18154308%2FDin-Dunia.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Ffrom-politics-to-movies-and-back-again-the-story-of-urdu-magazine-din-dunia%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20magazine%20stopped%20publishing%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20in%202020.%20Its%20last%20editor%2C%20Asif%20Fehmi%2C%20remembers%20the%20magazines%20trajectory%20%E2%80%93%20and%20hopes%20to%20give%20it%20another%20life%20soon.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A9%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Ffrom-politics-to-movies-and-back-again-the-story-of-urdu-magazine-din-dunia%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Not%20seeking%20a%20third%20term%20for%20political%20gains%2C%20but%20for%20benefit%20of%20India%3A%20PM%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708249813000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2024-02%2F11%2Ffull%2F1707653854-4461.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fpolitics%2Fnot-seeking-a-third-term-for-political-gains-but-for-benefit-of-india-pm-124021800281_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Addressing%20the%20BJP%20national%20convention%20here%2C%20Modi%20said%20the%20nation%20will%20now%20have%20to%20dream%20big%20and%20make%20big%20resolutions%20to%20make%20India%20a%20developed%20country%20by%202047%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A