2Fihcl-aims-to-strengthen-position-in-spiritual-tourism-to-add-more-hotels-124021800124_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20company%20currently%20has%2066%20hotels%20either%20operational%20or%20under%20development%20at%20spiritual%20destinations%2C%20including%20the%20latest%20hotspot%20Ayodhya%2C%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20grow%20the%20portfolio%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fihcl-aims-to-strengthen-position-in-spiritual-tourism-to-add-more-hotels-124021800124_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fihcl-aims-to-strengthen-position-in-spiritual-tourism-to-add-more-hotels-124021800124_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fihcl-aims-to-strengthen-position-in-spiritual-tourism-to-add-more-hotels-124021800124_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ayodhya%20Gets%20a%20Makeover%20%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%26nbsp%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F20160746%2Fimage-1778.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20fall%20of%201812%2C%20having%20successfully%20chased%20away%20Napoleon%E2%80%99s%20armies%2C%20Russian%20Czar%20Alexander%20the%20First%20decided%20to%20construct%20a%20grand%20temple%20for%20Christ%20in%20Moscow%20by%20way%20of%20thanksgiving.%20With%20the%20completion%20of%20the%20magnificent%20temple%20to%20Christ%20the%20Saviour%2C%20Moscow%20became%20the%20third%20Rome%20for%20the%20Russian%20public%2C%20writes%20Psakov%2C%20a%20sage%20and%20visionary.%20The%20holy%20temple%20project%20took%2045%20years%20to%20complete.%20It%20was%20consecrated%20in%20May%201883%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20the%20then%20czar%2C%20Alexander%20the%20Third%2C%20as%20a%20timeless%20sacred%20spot.%20It%20was%20a%20really%20%3Cem%3Edivya%20bhavya%3C%2Fem%3E%20piece%20of%20art%2C%20more%20than%2030%20stories%20tall%20with%20walls%20covered%20with%20frescos%2C%20a%20giant%20iconostasis%20that%20used%20422%20kilos%20of%20gold%2C%20and%20a%20main%20bell%20weighing%2024%20tonnes.%20Its%20interior%20was%20dazzling%20with%20gold%20silver%20and%20gems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20goddess%20of%20history%20it%20seems%2C%20had%20her%20own%20plans.%20The%20Bolshevik%20Revolution%20happened%20in%201917%2C%20the%20czar%20and%20his%20family%20were%20exiled%20and%20then%20killed.%20And%20then%20in%201931%20the%20all-powerful%20leader%20Stalin%20decided%20to%20raze%20it%20and%20erase%20the%20memory%20of%20the%20temple%20altogether.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20376px)%2085vw%2C%20376px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F05103945%2FIMG_1783.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mrinal%20Pande%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22376%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F05103945%2FIMG_1783.jpg%20525w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F05103945%2FIMG_1783-246x300.jpg%20246w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-642789%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22458%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOvernight%20the%20temple%20was%20made%20out%20of%20bounds%2C%20surrounded%20by%20barbed%20wire.%20When%20the%20demolishers%20had%20done%20whatever%20they%20could%2C%20only%20the%20shell%20remained%20of%20the%20once%20magnificent%20temple.%20All%20gold%20and%20gems%20and%20silk%20and%20velvet%20vestments%20embroidered%20with%20gold%20and%20silver%20threads%20were%20removed%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20cycle%20of%20erection%20and%20after%20some%20time%20shattering%20of%20grand%20places%20of%20worship%20and%20then%20again%20their%20re-erection%20has%20a%20long%20history%20in%20the%20world.%20Ayodhya%2C%20the%20latest%20city%20to%20be%20re-energised%20by%20the%20building%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%2C%20too%20has%20been%20through%20this%20cycle.%20Today%20few%20know%20that%20the%20holy%20site%20even%20pre-dates%20Ram.%20The%20Atharva%20Veda%20(second%20chapter)%20calls%20Ayodhya%20by%20its%20earlier%20Buddhist%20name%2C%20Saket.%20Buddhist%20text%20Divyavadaan%20corroborates%20this%20and%20says%20that%20Saket%20%C2%A0created%20itself%20(%3Cem%3ESvayamagata%2C%20swayamagata%20Saket%20iti%20uchyate%3C%2Fem%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20ancient%20folklore%2C%20the%20city%20that%20King%20Dashrath%20had%20built%20was%20buried%20under%20Sita%E2%80%99s%20curse.%20Several%20centuries%20later%20it%20was%20rediscovered%20by%20King%20Vikramaditya%20through%20a%20dream%20wherein%20the%20goddess%20of%20the%20city%20requested%20him%20to%20unearth%20her%20city.%20The%20king%20had%20it%20dug%20out%20from%20the%20depths%20of%20the%20earth.%20%C2%A0The%20vast%20pan-Indian%20popularity%20of%20the%20cult%20of%20Ram%20and%20Ayodhya%20as%20his%20holy%20birth%20place%20began%20only%20in%20the%2014th%20century%20with%20the%20Bhakti%20movement%20and%20its%20arrival%20up%20north%20in%20latter%20half%20of%2016th%3Cspan%3E%20century%3C%2Fspan%3E%20CE.%20Thereafter%20the%20Vaishnavite%20Ramanand%20sect%20and%20saint%20poet%20Tulsidas%20popularised%20it%20by%20their%20devotional%20poetry%20that%20portrayed%20Lord%20Ram%20of%20Ayodhya%20as%20the%20ideal%20Man-God%20(%3Cem%3EMaya%20Manushyam%20Hari%3C%2Fem%3E).%20Linking%20this%20with%20the%20recent%20makeover%20of%20Ayodhya%20by%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20and%20its%20formal%20installation%20of%20an%20idol%20of%20Ram%20as%20a%20young%20boy%20on%20January%2022%20is%20actually%20a%20journey%20into%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEstablishing%20an%20area%20as%20a%20holy%20spot%20and%20building%20and%20rebuilding%20monuments%20needs%20clever%20negotiators%20and%20publicists.%20So%20after%20the%20Ram%20cult%20got%20going%2C%20Hanumangarhi%2C%20the%20fortress%20of%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20most%20important%20emissary%2C%20came%20up%20and%20by%20the%2018th%20century%20became%20the%20natural%20meeting%20place%20for%20representatives%20of%20a%20slowly%20dying%20monarchy%20in%20Delhi%2C%20the%20empowered%20Awadh%20Durbar%20and%20the%20East%20India%20Company%20officials.%20All%20made%20important%20power-sharing%20deals%20with%20local%20mercenaries%20and%20bands%20of%20armed%20%3Cem%3Esadhus%3C%2Fem%3E%20for%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22In%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20Hailing%2C%20Sita%20Was%20Forgotten.%20Her%20Revival%20Would%20Have%20Symbolised%20Healing%20for%20Men%20and%20Women%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Freligion%2Fin-rams-hailing-sita-was-forgotten-her-revival-would-have-symbolised-healing-for-men-and-women%5C%22%3EIn%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20Hailing%2C%20Sita%20Was%20Forgotten.%20Her%20Revival%20Would%20Have%20Symbolised%20Healing%20for%20Men%20and%20Women%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20rebuilding%20of%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20at%20Ram%E2%80%99s%20birthplace%20began%20as%20an%20idea%20with%20immense%20political%20potential%20in%201992%2C%20the%20year%20of%20razing%20of%20the%20Babri%20mosque%20said%20to%20have%20been%20built%20by%20a%20general%2C%20Mir%20Baki%2C%20who%20had%20replaced%20an%20existing%20temple%20to%20build%20a%20mosque%20named%20after%20the%20victorious%20Mughal%20king%20Babar.%20Since%201992%2C%20Ayodhya%20became%20a%20political%20petridish%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20The%20mega%202019%20victory%20in%20the%20general%20elections%2C%20the%20rhetoric%20turned%20towards%20erecting%20a%20%3Cem%3Ebhavya%2C%20navya%2C%20divya%3C%2Fem%3E%20(grand%2C%20new%20and%20holy)%20temple%20there%20to%20Ram%2C%20both%20by%20way%20of%20thanksgiving%20and%20declaring%20the%20imminent%20arrival%20of%20a%20Hindutva-driven%20state.%20Soon%20it%20got%20the%20necessary%20judicial%20green%20signal%20to%20go%20ahead.%20Work%20was%20then%20speeded%20up%20to%20try%20and%20coincide%20the%20opening%20of%20the%20temple%20in%20January%202024%20with%20general%20election%20rallies%20scheduled%20just%20a%20few%20months%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Sangh%20%3Cem%3Eparivar%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20aided%20by%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Office%2C%20led%20everything%20from%20the%20front%20and%20at%20the%20installation%20ceremony%20of%20the%20Balak%20Ram%20statue%2C%20it%20was%20announced%20that%20Ram%20Lalla%20has%20returned%20after%20500%20years%20to%20his%20rightful%20place.%20As%20conch%20shells%20sounded%20and%20a%20thousand%20throats%20sang%20%3Cem%3Ebhajans%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20it%20was%20repeated%20again%20and%20again%20that%20Hindutva%20was%20the%20future%20and%20the%20core%20of%20India%20and%20the%20Ram%20Mandir%20would%20draw%20thousands%20of%20pilgrims%20from%20not%20just%20India%20but%20also%20foreign%20lands%20where%20diaspora%20Hindus%20still%20follow%20Hindutva.%20It%20was%20also%20underscored%20forcefully%20how%20this%20would%20invite%20capital%20investment%20in%20the%20state%20and%20Ayodhya%20in%20particular%20and%20generate%20jobs%20and%20opportunities%20for%20entrepreneurs%20and%20the%20tourist%20industry%20as%20a%20whole.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20who%20hail%20from%20Uttarakhand%2C%20recently%20christened%20Dev%20Bhumi%2C%20learnt%20early%20on%20how%20this%20works.%20The%20new%20pilgrims%20are%20religious%20tourists.%20The%20pilgrims%20had%20been%20coming%20to%20Ayodhya%20even%20earlier%2C%20but%20they%20were%20mostly%20simple%20rural%20folk%20or%20a%20few%20old%20couples%20with%20limited%20spending%20power%20and%20not%20much%20interest%20in%20worldly%20pursuits.%20The%20new%20tourists%20are%20young%20and%20will%20visit%20round%20the%20year%20in%20droves%20provided%20that%20pilgrimage%20trails%20have%20been%20made%20user%20friendly.%20No%20more%20smelly%20dharmshalas%20with%20bed%20bugs%20and%20bad%20food%20and%20temperamental%20Pandas%20for%20them.%20Photos%20of%20hotels%20and%20home%20stays%2C%20spas%20and%20food%20courts%20all%20along%20the%20routes%20must%20be%20available%20online%20for%20%E2%80%98customers%E2%80%99%20before%20the%20group%20bookings%20begin.%20And%20yes%2C%20it%20will%20bring%20in%20heap%20big%20bucks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20new%20species%20of%20pilgrims%20has%20also%20changed%20religion%20into%20an%20industry%20that%20follows%20pilgrims%E2%80%99%20algorithms%20keenly%20and%20creates%20bespoke%20exclusive%20packages.%20Old-style%20darshan%20and%20immersion%20in%20holy%20rivers%20are%20pass%C3%A9.%20The%20bespoke%20packages%20promise%20you%20%E2%80%9Ca%20mystic%20experience%20of%20a%20temple%2Fcity%20old-as-time!%E2%80%9D%20along%20with%20chances%20to%20do%20a%20bit%20of%20river%20rafting%20and%20air%20diving.%20The%20tourism%20promoters%20hand%20you%20addresses%20and%20coupons%20for%20buying%20souvenirs%20and%20holy%20waters%20and%20%3Cem%3Eprasadam%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20even%20send%20you%20maps%20dotted%20with%20selfie%20points.%20And%20of%20course%2C%20should%20the%20customers%20so%20wish%2C%20there%20will%20be%20camera%20crew%20available%20to%20capture%20the%20pilgrims%E2%80%99%20waggish%20ego.%20Honoured%20pilgrim%2Ftourists%20face%20none%20of%20the%20earlier%20multiple%20checkings%20by%20petty%20officials%20or%20long%20waits%20at%20toll%20plazas.%20Difficulties%2C%20as%20and%20when%20they%20arise%2C%20can%20be%20easily%20negotiated%20with%20some%20exchange%20of%20money%20and%20flashing%20official%20(read%20party)%20badges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22When%20Ravan%20Triumphs%20in%20Ayodhya%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fwhen-ravan-triumphs-in-ayodhya%5C%22%3EWhen%20Ravan%20Triumphs%20in%20Ayodhya%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20jury%20is%20still%20out%20on%20whether%20Amitabh%20Bachchan%20and%20sundry%20others%20who%20have%20already%20bought%20properties%20to%20go%20live%20in%20Ayodhya%2C%20will%20actually%20stay%20there.%20But%20the%20millennial%20pilgrims%E2%80%99%20progress%20in%20the%20age%20of%20global%20meltdowns%2C%20works%20along%20the%20evolution%20of%20the%20Amritkaal%20economy%20that%20has%20hard-wired%20them%20for%20planning%20for%20the%20coming%20year%20as%20they%20don%20their%20itinerant%20pilgrims%E2%80%99%20robes%20and%20get%20into%20their%20SUVs%20or%20leave%20for%20the%20newly%20built%20airport.%20Damn%20the%20carbon%20footprints%20or%20local%20water%20shortages%20that%20are%20routine%20now%20in%20temple%20towns.%20The%20neo-converts%20to%20Hindutva%3A%20scientists%20and%20engineers%2C%20doctors%2C%20IT%20czars%20and%20environmentalists%2C%20both%20desi%20and%20NRI%2C%20are%20all%20happy%20singing%20and%20partying%20to%20pop%20bhajans.%20The%20built%20in%20obsolescence%20within%20such%20tourism%20models%20does%20not%20interest%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Uttarakhand%2C%20we%20see%20the%20results%20clearly.%20As%20more%20and%20more%20pilgrims%20flock%20to%20Gangotri%20and%20Yamunotri%2C%20the%20glaciers%C2%A0%20recede.%20The%20broader%20the%20roads%2C%20the%20bigger%20the%20landslides%20during%20monsoons.%20Snow%20has%20already%20thinned%20to%20a%20stop%20in%20the%20entire%20Himalayan%20region.%20So%20watch%20out%2C%20Ayodhya%3B%20if%20you%20do%20not%20watch%20out%2C%20the%20place%20will%20lose%20its%20endearing%C2%A0%20informality%20and%20become%20another%20industrial%20city%20inviting%20skyscrapers%2C%20vast%20traffic%20jams%20and%20malls%20with%20food%20courts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEverybody%20knows%20this%2C%20but%20we%20are%20still%20witnessing%20the%20genetic%20inability%20of%20the%20rich%20and%20the%20powerful%20to%20deny%20the%20alarming%20reality%20of%20global%20warming.%20Inaugurating%20the%20first%20grand%20Hindu%20temple%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20built%20by%20the%20BAPS%20(Swamin%20Narayan%20sect)%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20described%20himself%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Cpriest%20of%20Ma%20Bharati%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20added%20how%20the%20grand%20temple%20in%20Abu%20Dhabi%20has%20enhanced%20Ayodhya%20joy.%20The%20BAPS%2C%20he%20predicted%2C%20will%20be%20a%20centre%20of%20communal%20harmony%20and%20global%20unity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20is%20about%20as%20good%20as%20it%20is%20going%20to%20get.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cstrong%3ESaakhi%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20Sunday%20column%20from%20Mrinal%20Pande%2C%20in%20which%20she%20writes%20of%20what%20she%20sees%20and%20also%20participates%20in.%20That%20has%20been%20her%20burden%20to%20bear%20ever%20since%20she%20embarked%20on%20a%20life%20as%20a%20journalist%2C%20writer%2C%20editor%2C%20author%20and%20as%20chairperson%20of%20Prasar%20Bharti.%20Her%20journey%20of%20being%20a%20witness-participant%20continues.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708236243000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F20160746%2Fimage-1778.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fayodhya-gets-a-makeover%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20new%20species%20of%20pilgrims%20has%20changed%20religion%20into%20an%20industry%20that%20follows%20pilgrims%E2%80%99%20algorithms%20keenly%20and%20creates%20bespoke%20exclusive%20packages.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A36%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fayodhya-gets-a-makeover%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Houthi%20attacks%20on%20Russian%20oil%20tankers%20complicate%20things%20for%20Indian%20refiners%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708235414000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-05%2F25%2Ffull%2F1684983083-75.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fhouthi-attacks-on-russian-oil-tankers-complicate-things-for-indian-refiners-124021800128_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Houthi%20attacks%20on%20Russian%20crude%20deliveries%20coincide%20with%20escalating%20US%20actions%20on%20ships%20carrying%20such%20crude%2C%20leading%20to%20double%20trouble%20for%20India%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fhouthi-attacks-on-russian-oil-tankers-complicate-things-for-indian-refiners-124021800128_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fhouthi-attacks-on-russian-oil-tankers-complicate-things-for-indian-refiners-124021800128_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Fhouthi-attacks-on-russian-oil-tankers-complicate-things-for-indian-refiners-124021800128_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Election%20Commission%20Will%20Follow%20Supreme%20Court's%20Directions%20on%20Electoral%20Bonds%3A%20CEC%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F25220532%2FScreenshot-2023-10-25-at-10.04.47%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EChief%20election%20commissioner%20Rajiv%20Kumar%20has%20said%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20will%20follow%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20directions%20on%20electoral%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20the%20first%20official%20body%20to%20comment%20on%20following%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20calling%20the%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20electoral%20bonds%20scheme%20unconstitutional%2C%20and%20asking%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%20to%20reveal%20details%20of%20all%20the%20donors%20who%20used%20the%20opaque%20scheme.%20The%20finance%20ministry%20and%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Office%20%E2%80%93%20both%20of%20which%20had%20key%20roles%20in%20drafting%20the%20scheme%20%E2%80%93%20have%20said%20nothing%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20its%20affidavit%20to%20the%20top%20court%2C%20the%20commission%20said%20it%20is%20in%20favour%20of%20transparency%20and%20when%20the%20order%20is%20issued%2C%20it%20will%20take%20action%20as%20directed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%E2%80%9D%20Kumar%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Felection-commission-to-follow-top-court-order-on-electoral-bonds-cec-rajiv-kumar-101708184521890.html%5C%22%3Esaid%20on%20Saturday%20(February%2017)%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felection-commission-has-no-comments-on-landmark-verdict-on-electoral-bonds-how-it-changed-its-stance%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20EC%20had%20taken%20contradictory%20positions%20on%20the%20schemes%20at%20different%20times.%20While%20it%20had%20expressed%20serious%20reservations%20initially%2C%20even%20calling%20it%20a%20%E2%80%9Cretrograde%20step%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%20then%20went%20on%20to%20back%20the%20scheme%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20argue%20that%20it%20should%20not%20be%20stayed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20response%20from%20the%20Modi%20government%20%E2%80%93%20which%20had%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpart-of-secret-ballot-how-the-modi-govt-backed-electoral-bonds-in-the-supreme-court%5C%22%3Evehemently%20argued%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20scheme%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20%E2%80%93%20so%20far%20has%20come%20from%20Union%20law%20minister%20Arjun%20Meghwal.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20government%20is%20%E2%80%9Cexamining%E2%80%9D%20the%20verdict%20and%20will%20decide%20whether%20to%20challenge%20the%20ruling.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20total%20number%20of%20electoral%20bonds%20worth%20Rs%2012%2C008%20crore%20sold%20between%202017-2018%20and%202022-2023%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Felectoral-bonds-are-illegal-now-but-who-benefited-for-the-6-years-they-lasted%5C%22%3EBJP%20received%20nearly%2055%25%20or%20Rs%206%2C564%20crore%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Congress%20has%20received%20just%209.5%25%20of%20all%20bonds%20sold%20in%20the%20five-year%20period%20at%20Rs%201%2C135%20crore.%20The%20Trinamool%20Congress%20has%20received%20Rs%201%2C096%20crore%20from%20electoral%20bonds%20in%20this%20same%20time%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708233793000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F25220532%2FScreenshot-2023-10-25-at-10.04.47%25E2%2580%25AFPM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commission-will-follow-supreme-courts-directions-on-electoral-bonds-cec%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%26quot%3BIn%20its%20affidavit%20to%20the%20top%20court%2C%20the%20commission%20said%20it%20is%20in%20favour%20of%20transparency%20and%20when%20the%20order%20is%20issued%2C%20it%20will%20take%20action%20as%20directed%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%26quot%3B%20Rajiv%20Kumar%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Felection-commission-will-follow-supreme-courts-directions-on-electoral-bonds-cec%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Difficult%20Conversations%20Await%20the%20INDIA%20Alliance%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18101256%2Findia-jandk.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20National%20Conference%20(NC)%20president%20Farooq%20Abdullah%20has%20thrown%20down%20a%20gauntlet%20with%20his%20remarks%20on%20seat-sharing%20arrangements%20with%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20for%20the%20upcoming%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20with%20reporters%20in%20Srinagar%20on%20Thursday%2C%20February%2015%2C%20Abdullah%20said%20that%20there%20are%20%E2%80%9Cno%20two%20opinions%E2%80%9D%20that%20the%20NC%2C%20which%20is%20part%20of%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%2C%20was%20going%20to%20contest%20the%202024%20general%20election%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20%E2%80%9Con%20the%20basis%20of%20our%20strength%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20remarks%20triggered%20speculations%20that%20after%20Nitish%20Kumar%2C%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20and%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%2C%20the%20NC%20president%20could%20be%20the%20latest%20addition%20to%20the%20list%20of%20political%20leaders%20who%20have%20deserted%20the%20fledgling%20INDIA%20alliance%20in%20recent%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOmar%20Abdullah%2C%20the%20NC%20vice-president%2C%20however%2C%20clarified%20that%20his%20party%20%E2%80%9Ccontinues%20to%20remain%20a%20member%20of%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%E2%80%9D.%20He%20claimed%20that%20the%20NC%20has%20had%20%E2%80%9Cinformal%20talks%E2%80%9D%20on%20seat-sharing%20with%20the%20Congress%2C%20which%20leads%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%2C%20while%20asserting%20that%20his%20party%20was%20going%20to%20contest%20on%20three%20out%20of%20six%20Lok%20Sabha%20constituencies%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20and%20Ladakh%20on%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20constituencies%20%E2%80%93%20Srinagar-Budgam%2C%20Baramulla-Kupwara%20and%20Anantnag-Rajouri%20%E2%80%93%20were%20won%20by%20the%20NC%20in%20the%202019%20parliamentary%20election.%20%E2%80%9CTherefore%2C%20the%20seats%20that%20are%20to%20be%20discussed%20are%20those%20held%20by%20the%20BJP%20(Jammu%2C%20Udhampur%20and%20Ladakh).%20We%20are%20firm%20on%20that%20position%2C%E2%80%9D%20Omar%20told%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20parliamentary%20constituencies%20are%20spread%20over%2012%20districts%20of%20the%20Kashmir%20valley%20and%20Pir%20Panjal%20region%20where%20all%20the%20three%20major%20constituents%20of%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20%E2%80%93%20Peoples%20Democratic%20Party%20(PDP)%2C%20NC%20and%20the%20Congress%20%E2%80%93%20have%20had%20a%20significant%20presence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%202014%20assembly%20election%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20the%20PDP%20had%20emerged%20as%20the%20single%20largest%20party%20with%2028%20seats%20(including%20three%20seats%20in%20the%20Pir%20Panjal%20region%20and%20the%20rest%20from%20Kashmir%20Valley)%20followed%20by%20the%20National%20Conference%20with%2015%20seats%20and%20the%20Congress%20with%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJammu-based%20editor%20and%20political%20analyst%20Zafar%20Choudhary%20said%20that%20the%20NC%E2%80%99s%20decision%20was%20unlikely%20to%20be%20acceptable%20to%20the%20allies%20of%20INDIA%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20%E2%80%93%20PDP%20and%20Congress%20%E2%80%93%20which%20could%20force%20a%20%E2%80%9Cfight%20to%20the%20finish%E2%80%9D%20between%20the%20three%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20BJP%20looks%20confident%20on%20its%20two%20traditional%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20(Jammu%20and%20Udhampur)%2C%20the%20absence%20of%20an%20NC-PDP-Congress%20alliance%20would%20clearly%20put%20the%20BJP%20in%20a%20position%20of%20advantage%20in%20Anantnag-Rajouri%20and%20Ladakh%20seats.%20An%20unofficial%20BJP%20ally%20could%20even%20emerge%20as%20a%20key%20competitor%20in%20north%20Kashmir%2C%E2%80%9D%20Choudhary%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERekha%20Chowdhary%2C%20former%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Jammu%2C%20believes%20that%20the%20NC%20is%20in%20a%20%E2%80%9Cbetter%20position%E2%80%9D%20electorally%20in%20Kashmir%20than%20other%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20main%20rival%20of%20the%20National%20Conference%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20which%20is%20the%20PDP%2C%20has%20become%20quite%20weak%20because%20of%20the%20exodus%20of%20some%20of%20its%20leaders%20and%20other%20factors.%20The%20PDP%20has%20lost%20its%20confidence%20and%20the%20party%20is%20not%20in%20a%20position%20where%20it%20can%20negotiate%20seat-sharing%20with%20other%20INDIA%20partners%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZafar%20Choudhary%20agreed%20that%20the%20PDP%20has%20been%20suffering%20politically%20because%20of%20its%20alliance%20with%20the%20BJP%20in%202015.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20subsequent%20events%20including%20government%20formation%20crisis%20following%20Mufti%20Sayeed%E2%80%99s%20death%2C%202016%20civilian%20unrest%2C%20fall%20of%20government%20in%202018%20and%20the%20casual%20handling%20of%20the%20dismissal%20of%20assembly%20project%20the%20PDP%20in%20a%20poor%20light%20and%2C%20consequently%2C%20the%20NC%20in%20a%20better%20position%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20senior%20PDP%20leader%20said%20that%20there%20was%20%E2%80%9Cno%20question%E2%80%9D%20that%20his%20party%20was%20going%20to%20stay%20out%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20contest%20but%20%E2%80%9Cour%20foremost%20goal%20is%20unity%E2%80%9D.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20party%20was%20in%20the%20midst%20of%20a%20%E2%80%9Cconsultation%20process%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20won%E2%80%99t%20take%20a%20decision%20under%20pressure%20or%20in%20a%20hurry%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20question%20of%20just%20the%20elections%20but%20how%20to%20strengthen%20our%20voice%20at%20the%20national%20level%20and%20in%20the%20parliament%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20PDP%20leader%2C%20who%20served%20as%20a%20minister%20in%20the%20PDP-BJP%20coalition%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20PDP%20leader%20said%20that%20the%20party%20will%20%E2%80%9Cideally%20want%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20a%20united%20voice%E2%80%9D%20against%20the%20BJP%20from%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20if%20one%20of%20the%20constituents%20does%20not%20want%20to%20yield%20space%20to%20others%2C%20we%20would%20feel%20our%20attempts%20from%202019%20to%20forge%20unity%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20first%20in%20the%20form%20of%20Gupkar%20Alliance%20and%20then%20the%20INDIA%20alliance%2C%20have%20failed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZafar%20Choudhary%20said%20that%20the%20Gupkar%20alliance%20between%20the%20three%20parties%20did%20not%20work%20electorally%20as%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%202020%20District%20Development%20Council%20(DDC)%20elections%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20parties%20also%20realised%20that%20they%20compete%20on%20the%20same%20electoral%20landscape%20for%20their%20individual%20survival%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20then%2C%20Omar%20has%20believed%20in%20separating%20the%20electoral%20and%20ideological%20agenda%20within%20the%20Gupkar%20alliance.%20In%20November%202022%2C%20the%20NC%20released%20a%20list%20of%2046%20leaders%20for%20as%20many%20constituencies%20in%20Kashmir%20calling%20them%20Constituency-Incharge.%20This%20was%20a%20clear%20message%20to%20the%20allies%20that%20there%20was%20no%20scope%20for%20alliance%20whenever%20assembly%20elections%20are%20held.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20that%20Dr%20Abdullah%20and%20Omar%20have%20%E2%80%9Cconsistently%20held%20divergent%20views%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20alliance%2C%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20Dr%20Abdullah%20has%20always%20reiterated%20the%20primacy%20of%20the%20Gupkar%20Alliance%2C%20Omar%20has%20taken%20more%20practical%20actions%20to%20consolidate%20on%20a%20post-2019%20advantage%20uniquely%20available%20to%20the%20National%20Conference.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERekha%20Chowdharyy%20said%20that%20the%20NC%E2%80%99s%20performance%20in%20the%20DDC%20election%20may%20have%20contributed%20to%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cconfidence%E2%80%9D%20about%20its%20performance%20in%20the%20upcoming%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20commitment%20(to%20INDIA%20alliance)%20is%20not%20entrenched%20in%20the%20political%20parties%20in%20Kashmir.%20No%20party%20will%20sacrifice%20its%20interests%20for%20the%20interests%20of%20any%20alliance.%20While%20Mehbooba%20Mufti%20is%20more%20committed%20to%20the%20INDIA%20and%20Gupkar%20alliances%20for%20the%20survival%20of%20her%20party%2C%20NC%20is%20not%20dependent%20on%20either%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20the%20media%20in%20Srinagar%2C%20Omar%20said%20that%20political%20parties%20have%20to%20make%20%E2%80%9Csmall%20sacrifices%20%E2%80%A6%20for%20a%20bigger%20objective%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20objective%20of%20INDIA%20alliance%20is%20to%20weaken%20each%20other%2C%20the%20National%20Conference%20is%20ready%20for%20negotiations.%20What%20purpose%20will%20a%20weakened%20National%20Conference%20serve%20if%20the%20aim%20is%20to%20defeat%20the%20BJP%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708231397000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18101256%2Findia-jandk.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdifficult-conversations-await-the-india-alliance-in-jk%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22With%20the%20National%20Conference%20declaring%20that%20it%20intends%20to%20contest%20in%20the%20three%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20it%20currently%20holds%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%20and%20Ladakh%2C%20seat-sharing%20talks%20may%20be%20a%20tricky%20affair.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdifficult-conversations-await-the-india-alliance-in-jk%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Former%20Thai%20Prime%20Minister%20Thaksin%20freed%20on%20parole%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708230556000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FA20F%2Fproduction%2F_132678414_thaksin_getty.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-68329953%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Thaksin%20Shinawatra%2C%20one%20of%20Thailand's%20most%20divisive%20figures%2C%20was%20convicted%20last%20year%20on%20corruption%20charges.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A103%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-68329953%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-68329953.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-68329953.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20'New%20India'%20Militates%20Against%20the%20Idea%20of%20India%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18091404%2FWrestlers_Protest_India_2023.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20is%20an%20excerpt%20from%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20Practices%20of%20the%20State%3A%20Muslims%2C%20Law%20and%20Violence%20in%20India%3Cem%3E%20by%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0%20%3Cem%3ETanweer%20Fazal%20(Three%20Essays%20Collective%2C%202024).%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20year%202019%20marked%20a%20watershed%20in%20the%20biography%20of%20the%20Indian%20state.%20The%20resounding%20victory%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Right%20in%20the%20parliamentary%20elections%2C%20second%20one%20in%20continuation%2C%20was%20followed%20by%20a%20series%20of%20parliamentary%20amendments%20and%20enactments%20directed%20towards%20inverting%20constitutional%20guarantees%20and%20protections%20that%20the%20polity%20had%20until%20now%20offered%20to%20its%20minority%20citizens.%20The%20criminalisation%20of%20triple%20talaq%2C%20the%20abrogation%20of%20Article%20370%20and%20the%20enactment%20of%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20(2019)%E2%80%94patently%20contentious%20and%20perilous%E2%80%94were%20expeditiously%20executed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENeither%20judicial%20challenges%20nor%20the%20wave%20of%20protests%20that%20sprung%20up%20in%20many%20parts%20of%20the%20country%20deterred%20the%20government.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20judiciary%20too%20joined%20in%20this%20new%20drift%20in%20the%20idea%20of%20the%20Republic%20by%20two%20pronouncements%20of%20far-reaching%20consequences.%20The%20Supreme%20Court-directed%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizens%20published%20the%20final%20list%20of%20citizens%20in%20Assam%2C%20which%20ultimately%20left%20nearly%20two%20million%20residents%20of%20the%20state%2C%20mostly%20Bengalis%2C%20stateless.%20In%20addition%2C%20a%20five-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Apex%20Court%20handed%20over%20the%20title%20of%20the%20site%20of%20the%20demolished%20Babri%20mosque%20for%20the%20construction%20of%20the%20Ram%20temple.%20In%20August%202020%2C%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20laid%20the%20foundation%20stone%20of%20the%20Ram%20temple%20in%20the%20company%20of%20the%20RSS%20chief%2C%20an%20organisation%20indicted%20for%20the%20demolition%20of%20the%20mosque%20in%201992.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18090619%2FTF-COVER_page-0001.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18090619%2FTF-COVER_page-0001.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18090619%2FTF-COVER_page-0001-300x236.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18090619%2FTF-COVER_page-0001-1024x806.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697671%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22944%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECover%20page%20of%20the%20book%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EThe%20Practices%20of%20the%20State%3A%20Muslims%2C%20Law%20and%20Violence%20in%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98%20by%C2%A0Tanweer%20Fazal%20(Three%20Essays%20Collective%2C%202024)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20%E2%80%98new%20normal%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20illusive%20%E2%80%98idea%20of%20India%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20%E2%80%98new%20normal%E2%80%99%2C%20it%20is%20argued%2C%20militates%20against%20the%20idea%20of%20India%20%E2%80%94%20the%20vision%20of%20a%20plural%20society%2C%20of%20a%20non-denominational%20secular%20republic%20that%20its%20founders%20embraced%20and%20set%20out%20to%20realise%20once%20unfettered%20of%20colonial%20chains.%20For%20many%20commentators%2C%20this%20plummeting%20of%20the%20Indian%20core%20into%20a%20%E2%80%98monochromatic%20nationalism%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20new%20one%2C%20and%20certainly%20%E2%80%98un-Indian%E2%80%99.%20In%20the%20late%201990s%2C%20Sunil%20Khilnani%2C%20in%20his%20treatise%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98idea%20of%20India%E2%80%99%2C%20saw%20a%20diversity%20of%20opinions%2C%20ideas%20and%20styles%20as%20constitutive%20of%20Indian%20nationalism%20%E2%80%94%20%E2%80%98a%20dhoti%20with%20endless%20folds%E2%80%99.%20A%20decade%20later%2C%20when%20the%20politics%20of%20Hindutva%20had%20begun%20baying%20for%20blood%2C%20Khilnani%20clarified%20that%20the%20plural%20idea%20of%20India%20had%20within%20its%20store%2C%20%E2%80%98conceptions%20that%20sought%20to%20singularise%E2%80%99%20Indian%20diversity%2C%20and%20%E2%80%98make%20it%20a%20narrower%20place%E2%80%99.%20This%20politics%20had%20made%20Gujarat%20the%20%E2%80%98calendar%20girl%20of%20big%20business%E2%80%99%2C%20also%20the%20%E2%80%98purveyor%E2%80%99%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98most%20chauvinistic%20and%20poisonous%20politics%E2%80%99%2C%20he%20argued%20(2012%2C%20p.%203).%20He%2C%20however%2C%20still%20continued%20to%20rest%20his%20hopes%20on%20democracy%20%E2%80%94%20an%20accomplishment%20of%20the%20founders%20of%20the%20founders%20that%20still%20stood%20tall%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20broken%2C%20ragged%20histories%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20neighbours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20contrast%20was%20invariably%20drawn%20with%20Pakistan%2C%20which%20owed%20its%20genesis%20to%20religious%20nationalism%2C%20and%20had%20miserably%20failed%20to%20hold%20together.%20Khilnani%20feared%20that%20India%20might%20turn%20into%20a%20Hindu%20Pakistan%20if%20a%20politics%20centred%20on%20cultural%20supremacy%20was%20allowed%20to%20prevail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20years%20later%20when%20the%20liberal%20icon%20Shashi%20Tharoor%20echoed%20the%20same%20fear%2C%20he%20received%20a%20terrible%20backlash%20from%20the%20Hindu%20public%2C%20purportedly%2C%20for%20uttering%20the%20words%20Hindu%20and%20Pakistan%20in%20a%20single%20breath.%20But%20such%20comparisons%20with%20Pakistan%20or%20Taliban%20are%20not%20so%20uncommon%20in%20India%20today.%20The%20allegory%20is%20invoked%20to%20contrast%20the%20intrinsic%20Indian%20ethos%20of%20tolerance%20as%20against%20the%20fanaticism%20of%20its%20neighbour.%20The%20roots%20of%20an%20archetypal%20Indian%20tolerance%20are%20then%20traced%20to%20the%20ancient%20philosophy%20and%20Hindu%20view%20of%20the%20self%20and%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20celebrated%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Argumentative%20Indian%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2005)%2C%20Amartya%20Sen%20traces%20the%20roots%20of%20Indian%20pluralism%20to%20the%20co-existence%20of%20competing%20paths%20to%20truth%20in%20the%20Rig%20Veda.%20The%20crux%20of%20Tharoor%E2%80%99s%20critique%20of%20Hindutva%20in%20%3Cem%3EWhy%20I%20am%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20(2018)%20is%20how%20the%20former%20defies%20the%20inherent%20diversity%20of%20thought%20and%20plurality%20of%20practices%20that%20is%20characteristic%20of%20Hinduism.%20Far%20from%20embarrassing%20the%20proponents%20of%20militant%20Hindutva%2C%20this%20project%20ends%20up%20reinforcing%20the%20distortions%20that%20imaginaries%20of%20Hindu%20nationalism%20hinge%20on%20%E2%80%94%20a%20tolerant%20and%20accommodating%20Hindu%20whose%20Hinduness%20is%20intrinsic%20to%20Indian%20tolerance.%20This%20imaginary%20of%20the%20Hindu%20Indian%20then%20stands%20in%20contrast%20to%20portrayals%20of%20the%20treacherous%20and%20bigoted%20Muslim.%20The%20source%20of%20violence%2C%20the%20agent%20provocateur%20is%20then%20the%20Muslim%20%E2%80%94%20the%20sword-bearing%2C%20beef-eating%20Jihadist.%20%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20this%20vision%20of%20a%20plural%20and%20diverse%20India%20was%20so%20deeply%20embedded%20in%20its%20heart%20and%20soul%2C%20how%20did%20the%20idea%20unravel%20in%20no%20time%3F%20How%20come%20the%20institutions%20that%20it%20founded%20fell%20in%20line%2C%20offering%20not%20a%20modicum%20of%20resistance%3F%20Of%20all%20the%20recent%20breaches%20in%20the%20foundational%20idea%20of%20India%2C%20one%20with%20the%20most%20far-reaching%20ramifications%20is%20the%20alteration%20in%20the%20citizenship%20law%20that%20allows%20faith%20to%20make%20a%20surreptitious%20entry%20in%20the%20provisions%20for%20according%20citizenship%20to%20immigrants.%20It%20despatches%20a%20message%20loud%20and%20clear%2C%20that%20blood%20and%20belongingness%20will%20be%20a%20determinant%20of%20Indian%20nationality%20%E2%80%94%20jus%20sanguinus%20as%20against%20jus%20solis%20(the%20right%20of%20soil%20determined%20by%20birth).%20Undoubtedly%2C%20the%20secular%20foundation%20of%20Indian%20nationhood%20is%20at%20stake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20loud%20and%20vociferous%20protests%20that%20followed%20its%20enactment%20remained%20confined%20to%20Muslim%20localities%20where%20too%20the%20repression%20of%20the%20state%20machinery%20was%20felt%20most%20viscerally.%20Even%20though%20a%20section%20of%20the%20intelligentsia%20and%20the%20secular%20civil%20society%20enlisted%20its%20support%2C%20a%20cross-sectional%20participation%20was%20evidently%20absent.%20Why%20is%20there%20no%20popular%20outcry%20when%20the%20very%20foundational%20principle%20of%20post-ndependent%20India%20is%20in%20tatters%20today%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20contrary%2C%20what%20is%20discernible%20is%20virtually%20an%20endorsement%20from%20large%20sections%20of%20the%20old%20and%20new%20middle%20classes%2C%20as%20much%20as%20from%20the%20poor%20and%20the%20rich.%20The%20%E2%80%98principal%20carrier%E2%80%99%20of%20this%20%E2%80%98idea%20of%20India%E2%80%99%20that%20revels%20in%20old%20glories%20drawn%20from%20the%20mythical%20Hindu%20past%20is%20not%20only%20the%20liberal%20mainstream%20of%20Indian%20intellectual%20life%2C%20but%20%E2%80%98extends%20much%20further%20%E2%80%A6%20to%20the%20left%20of%20this%20mainstream%E2%80%99%20(Perry%20Anderson%2C%202015%2C%20p.%209).%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%E2%80%A6%3Cbr%3E%5CnInstead%20of%20lamenting%20the%20loss%20of%20good%20old%20days%2C%20a%20much%20more%20rewarding%20experience%20would%20be%20to%20excavate%20the%20past%20in%20order%20to%20comprehend%20the%20present.%20What%20turn%20of%20events%2C%20processes%2C%20relics%20and%20forces%20of%20history%20abetted%20the%20rise%20of%20this%20brute%20majoritarianism%3F%20In%20order%20to%20do%20so%2C%20a%20closer%20interrogation%20of%20the%20foundational%20ideas%20is%20perhaps%20obligatory.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708228108000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F18091404%2FWrestlers_Protest_India_2023.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhow-new-india-militates-against-the-idea-of-india%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Tanweer%20Fazal's%20latest%20book%20'The%20Practices%20of%20the%20State%3A%20Muslims%2C%20Law%20and%20Violence%20in%20India'%20brings%20into%20perspective%20how%20the%20vision%20of%20a%20pluralist%20India%20has%20been%20turned%20into%20monochromatic%20nationalism%20over%20the%20last%2010%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fhow-new-india-militates-against-the-idea-of-india%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22West%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20Michelin-starred%20cuisine%20wows%20London%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708224602000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F64E3%2Fproduction%2F_132672852_akoko_team976.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-68300006%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22African%20fine%20dining%20is%20often%20overlooked%2C%20but%20now%20restaurants%20are%20getting%20their%20just%20deserts.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A201%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-africa-68300006%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2