FImage-7.jpg%20849w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17170120%2FImage-7-212x300.jpg%20212w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17170120%2FImage-7-724x1024.jpg%20724w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697657%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EImage%208%3A%20Extract%20from%20BEL%E2%80%99s%20Complete%20Specifications%20of%20VVPAT%20machine%20submitted%20to%20the%20Patents%20Office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhich%20is%20the%20vote%20that%20must%20be%20counted%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReaders%2C%20wearied%20by%20all%20these%20technical%20details%2C%20may%20ask-%20%E2%80%9Cwhat%20is%20the%20point%20of%20all%20this%20argumentation%20and%20evidence-splashing%3F%E2%80%9D%20Well%2C%20the%20point%20is%20very%20simple%20and%20goes%20to%20the%20very%20heart%20of%20the%20demand%20made%20by%20several%20opposition%20political%20parties%20and%20civil%20society%20groups%20like%20the%20Citizens%20Commission%20on%20Elections%20(CCE)-%20all%20VVPAT%20slips%20must%20be%20counted%20rather%20than%20a%20small%20sample%20of%20five%20randomly%20chosen%20VVPAT%20units%20which%20the%20ECI%20has%20defended%20to%20be%20scientifically%20of%20adequate%20size%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20in%20its%20reply%20to%20FAQ%20%2362.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20context%20of%20electronic%20voting%20which%20is%20the%20%E2%80%9Cvote%E2%80%9D%20that%20must%20be%20counted%20on%20counting%20day%20after%20polling%20is%20over-%20is%20it%20the%20candidates%E2%80%99%20tally%20of%20votes%20as%20calculated%20by%20the%20CU%20or%20the%20VVPAT%20slips%20which%20the%20voters%20see%20and%20verify%20to%20their%20satisfaction%3F%20This%20is%20the%20question%20that%20many%20opposition%20leaders%20and%20CCE%20have%20posed%20to%20the%20ECI.%20ECI%20deals%20with%20this%20issue%20at%20FAQ%20%2363%20in%20this%20manner%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CQ63.%20The%20ECI%20has%20to%20define%20which%20one%20is%20true%20representation%20of%20the%20will%20of%20the%20voter%3F%20Vote%20recorded%20on%20Control%20Unit%20or%20voter%20verified%20SLIP%20in%20VVPAT%3F%20If%20Counting%20is%20based%20on%20the%20Control%20Unit%20count%20what%20is%20the%20use%20of%20Verifiable%20paper%20SLIP%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EAns.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20system%20of%20VVPAT%20has%20been%20introduced%20only%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20greater%20transparency%20and%20enhancing%20the%20confidence%20of%20voters%20by%20way%20of%20immediate%20verification%20of%20the%20printed%20ballot%20slip%20having%20the%20chosen%20candidate%E2%80%99s%20Name%2C%20Serial%20Number%20and%20Symbol%20and%20recording%20of%20vote%20in%20the%20Control%20Unit.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EAs%20per%20existing%20legislation%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3ERule%2056C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Eof%20the%20Conduct%20of%20Elections%20(Amendment)%20Rules%20clearly%20states%20that%20after%20the%20returning%20officer%20is%20satisfied%20that%20a%20voting%20machine%20has%20not%20been%20tampered%20with%2C%20he%20shall%20have%20the%20votes%20counted%20by%20pressing%20the%20appropriate%20button%20marked%20%E2%80%9CResult%E2%80%9D%20provided%20in%20the%20control%20unit%20whereby%20the%20total%20votes%20polled%20and%20votes%20polled%20by%20each%20candidate%20shall%20be%20displayed%20in%20respect%20of%20each%20candidate%20on%20the%20display%20panel%20provided%20for%20the%20purpose%20in%20the%20unit.%20The%20candidate%20wise%20result%20so%20obtained%20from%20all%20control%20units%20used%20in%20the%20election%20is%20to%20be%20tabulated%20in%20a%20result%20sheet%20in%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3EForm%2020%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Eand%20the%20particulars%20so%20entered%20in%20the%20result%20sheet%20announced.%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EContesting%20candidates%20have%20the%20opportunity%20to%20request%20for%20the%20VVPAT%20slip%20count%20under%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3ERule%2056D%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3Eof%20the%20Conduct%20of%20Elections%20Rules%2C%201961%20after%20completion%20of%20counting%20of%20votes%20from%20the%20EVMs.%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3ERule%2056D%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E(4)%20(b)%20clearly%20states%20that%20in%20case%20of%20a%20discrepancy%20between%20the%20Electronic%20Count%20in%20the%20Control%20Unit%20and%20the%20ballot%20slip%20count%20of%20the%20VVPAT%2C%20the%20VVPAT%20slip%20count%20shall%20prevail.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20at%20paragraph%20%3Cstrong%3Eno.%2000116%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20of%20the%20Complete%20Specifications%20submitted%20to%20the%20Patents%20Office%20BEL%20makes%20the%20following%20assertion%20about%20what%20is%20the%20vote%20(see%20%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EImage%209%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ebelow)%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3E%5B00116%5D%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20this%20manner%2C%20proposed%20system%20can%20faithfully%20record%20the%20%3Cu%3Edigital%20choice%20(vote%20being%20cast)%20of%20the%20voter%20(using%20the%20BU%20of%20the%20associated%20EVM)%3C%2Fu%3E%20%3Cu%3Ein%20form%20of%20a%20printed%20ballot%20slip%20that%20is%20directly%20and%20easily%20understood%20by%20the%20voter%20as%20soon%20as%20the%20voter%20has%20exercised%20his%2Fher%20digital%20choice%3C%2Fu%3E%3B%20and%20thereafter%20store%20the%20printed%20ballot%20slip%20at%20a%20secure%20location%20for%20further%20audit%20if%20required.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fem%3E(emphasis%20supplied)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIs%20it%20not%20the%20digital%20choice%20of%20the%20voter%20as%20recorded%20by%20the%20VVPAT%20on%20paper%20which%20must%20be%20counted%2C%20and%20not%20merely%20the%20electronic%20data%20recorded%20in%20the%20CU%20which%20the%20voter%20will%20never%20get%20to%20see%20at%20the%20polling%20booth%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17170454%2FImage-9.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22849%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17170454%2FImage-9.jpg%20849w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17170454%2FImage-9-212x300.jpg%20212w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F17170454%2FImage-9-724x1024.jpg%20724w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-697660%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%3A%20Extract%20from%20BEL%E2%80%99s%20Complete%20Specifications%20of%20the%20VVPAT%20machine%20submitted%20to%20the%20Patents%20Office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConclusion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20beginning%20of%20this%20piece%2C%20I%20raised%20these%20questions-%20%E2%80%9Ccan%20it%20then%20be%20said%20that%20the%20voter%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20know%20is%20limited%20to%20accessing%20details%20about%20the%20public%20character%20of%20electoral%20candidates%20and%20nothing%20more%20relating%20to%20the%20electoral%20process%3F%20Does%20it%20not%20extend%20to%20seeking%20adequate%20knowledge%20about%20the%20current%20voting%20system%20which%20is%20facilitated%20through%20machines%20unlike%20the%20paper-based%20system%20that%20was%20the%20primary%20balloting%20method%20until%20a%20decade%20ago%3F%20When%20I%20began%20writing%20this%20piece%2C%20these%20questions%20were%20open-ended.%20However%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Constitution%20Bench%20which%20struck%20down%20the%20electoral%20bonds%20route%20of%20funding%20political%20parties%20has%20answered%20them%20conclusively.%20While%20concurring%20with%20the%20judgement%20(%3Cem%3EAssociation%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20%26amp%3B%20Ar.%2C%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E)%20authored%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20D%20Y%20Chandrachud%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20Bench%2C%20Justice%20Khanna%20in%20his%20separate%20opinion%20says-%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9C19.%20%3Cu%3EThe%20right%20to%20vote%20is%20a%20constitutional%20and%20statutory%20right%2C%E2%80%A6%20grounded%20in%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20as%20the%20casting%20of%20a%20vote%20amounts%20to%20expression%20of%20an%20opinion%20by%20the%20voter%E2%80%A6%20The%20citizens%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20know%20stems%20from%20this%20very%20right%2C%20as%20meaningfully%20exercising%20choice%20by%20voting%20requires%20information%3C%2Fu%3E.%20Representatives%20elected%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20votes%20cast%20in%20their%20favour%2C%20enact%20new%2C%20and%20amend%20existing%20laws%2C%20and%20when%20in%20power%2C%20take%20policy%20decisions.%20%3Cu%3EAccess%20to%20information%20which%20can%20materially%20shape%20the%20citizens%E2%80%99%20choice%20is%20necessary%20for%20them%20to%20have%20a%20say%20in%20how%20their%20lives%20are%20affected%3C%2Fu%3E.%20%3Cu%3EThus%2C%20the%20right%20to%20know%20is%20paramount%20for%20free%20and%20fair%20elections%20and%20democracy%3C%2Fu%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%20(emphasis%20supplied)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20Chandrachud%20records%20the%20views%20of%20the%20Constitution%20Bench%20about%20the%20importance%20of%20the%20voters%E2%80%99%20right%20to%20know%20in%20the%20following%20words%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9C77.%20The%20following%20principles%20can%20be%20deduced%20from%20the%20decisions%20of%20this%20Court%20in%20ADR%20(supra)%20and%20PUCL%20(supra)%3A%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cem%3E%20The%20right%20to%20information%20of%20voters%20which%20is%20traced%20to%20Article%2019(1)(a)%20is%20built%20upon%20the%20jurisprudence%20of%20both%20the%20first%20and%20the%20second%20phases%20in%20the%20evolution%20of%20the%20doctrine%2C%20identified%20above.%20%3Cu%3EThe%20common%20thread%20of%20reasoning%20which%20runs%20through%20both%20the%20first%20and%20the%20second%20phases%20is%20that%20information%20which%20furthers%20democratic%20participation%20must%20be%20provided%20to%20citizens.%20Voters%20have%20a%20right%20to%20information%20which%20would%20enable%20them%20to%20cast%20their%20votes%20rationally%20and%20intelligently%20because%20voting%20is%20one%20of%20the%20foremost%20forms%20of%20democratic%20participation%3C%2Fu%3E%3B%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%20(emphasis%20supplied)%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20issues%20discussed%20above%20are%20just%20a%20sample%20of%20the%20multiple%20doubts%20that%20crop%20up%20when%20the%20ECI%E2%80%99s%20answers%20to%20FAQs%20are%20compared%20with%20the%20contents%20of%20other%20publicly%20available%20documents%20about%20the%20EVM-VVPAT%20combo.%20Therefore%2C%20it%20must%20be%20said%2C%20our%20doubts%20will%20not%20go%20away%20by%20simply%20admonishing%20or%20ignoring%20them.%20The%20levels%20of%20transparency%20that%20the%20ECI%20has%20adopted%20are%20hopelessly%20inadequate%20to%20meet%20the%20very%20high%20standards%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20has%20set%20for%20our%20right%20to%20know%2C%20as%20citizen-voters.%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EVenkatesh%20Nayak%20is%20Director%2C%20Commonwealth%20Human%20Rights%20Initiative%2C%20New%20Delhi.%20All%20facts%20narrated%20above%20are%20in%20the%20public%20domain.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708172596000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F02%2F10211621%2FEffect-2024-02-10T202212.238.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhy-election-commissions-faqs-on-evm-vvpats-dont-clear-cloud-of-suspicion-over-electoral-process%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20levels%20of%20transparency%20that%20the%20Election%20Commission%20have%20adopted%20are%20hopelessly%20inadequate%20to%20meet%20the%20very%20high%20standards%20that%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20has%20set%20for%20our%20right%20to%20know%2C%20as%20citizen-voters.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fwhy-election-commissions-faqs-on-evm-vvpats-dont-clear-cloud-of-suspicion-over-electoral-process%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'No%20preparation'%20for%20influx%20of%20Palestinians%20at%20Rafah%20border%20-%20Egypt's%20foreign%20minister%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708171860000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F02%2F768x432%2Fskynews-rafah-palestinians_6458781.jpg%3F20240217134902%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fisrael-hamas-war-no-preparation-whatsoever-for-influx-of-palestinian-civilians-at-gazas-rafah-border-crossing-says-egypts-foreign-minister-13073667%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Egyptian%20foreign%20minister%20has%20denied%20reports%20his%20country%20is%20preparing%20for%20an%20influx%20of%20refugees%20as%20Palestinians%20in%20Rafah%20face%20an%20expected%20Israeli%20ground%20offensive.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1037%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fisrael-hamas-war-no-preparation-whatsoever-for-influx-of-palestinian-civilians-at-gazas-rafah-border-crossing-says-egypts-foreign-minister-13073667%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fisrael-hamas-war-no-preparation-whatsoever-for-influx-of-palestinian-civilians-at-gazas-rafah-border-crossing-says-egypts-foreign-minister-13073667%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fisrael-hamas-war-no-preparation-whatsoever-for-influx-of-palestinian-civilians-at-gazas-rafah-border-crossing-says-egypts-foreign-minister-13073667%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Backstory%20%7C%20Moral%20of%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%20Story%3A%20Information%20Is%20Essential%20for%20Democracy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F10%2F30183824%2FIMG_4397-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ETurning%20points%20have%20come%20but%20rarely%20in%20the%20ten%20years%20of%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%2C%20given%20its%20astounding%20success%20in%20maintaining%20an%20iron-clad%2C%20surveillance-driven%20grip%20on%20every%20institution%20in%20the%20country.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20verdict%20of%20February%2015%20that%20outlawed%20electoral%20bonds%20is%20emphatically%20one%20of%20them%2C%20and%20needs%20to%20be%20recognised%20as%20another%20chance%20that%20has%20been%20given%20to%20us%2C%20as%20Indians%2C%20to%20redeem%20our%20besmirched%20republic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20moment%20stands%20as%20testimony%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20capacity%20to%20assert%20itself%2C%20something%20we%20felt%20it%20had%20become%20incapable%20of%20doing.%C2%A0%20It%20remembered%20its%20obligations%20to%20the%20Constitution%20and%20to%20one%20of%20its%20foundational%20principles%20%E2%80%93%20Article%2019%201(a)%20guaranteeing%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression%20as%20well%20as%20the%20concomitant%20right%20to%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20is%2C%20would%20the%20court%20have%20done%20the%20right%20thing%20and%20outlawed%20electoral%20bonds%20if%20it%20had%20not%20been%20for%20the%20dogged%20resistance%20of%20an%20unsung%2C%20often%20attacked%20and%20abused%20tribe%2C%20sometimes%20derided%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9CRTI-%3Cem%3Ewallahs%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%3F%20It%20is%20these%20women%20and%20men%20who%20kept%20up%20their%20date%20with%20the%20courts%2C%20%3Cem%3Etarikh-pe-tarikh%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20along%20with%20their%20praetorian%20guard%20of%20constitutional%20lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20journalist%20Nitin%20Sethi%2C%20tweeted%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20wasn%E2%80%99t%201%20or%202%20people%20or%20organisations.%20Many%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSauravDassss%5C%22%3E%40SauravDas%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20Common%20Cause%2C%20Anjali%20B%20and%20her%20colleagues%2C%20Venkatesh%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmediatrack_in%5C%22%3E%40mediatrack%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fpoonamjourno%5C%22%3E%40poonamjourno%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAmannama%5C%22%3E%40Amannama%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSharanyaHK%5C%22%3E%40SharanyaHK%3C%2Fa%3E.%20With%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FCommodoreBatra%5C%22%3E%40CommodoreBatra%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26amp%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fadrspeaks%5C%22%3E%40adrspeaks%3C%2Fa%3E%20leading.%20It%20took%20a%20village.%20But%20it%20ain%E2%80%99t%20over%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20did%20this%20right%20from%20the%20days%20when%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20was%20introduced%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Finance%20Bill%20in%20the%20Budget%20of%20February%202017.%20Within%20a%20span%20of%20six%20months%2C%20the%20lead%20petitioners%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20and%20Common%20Cause%2C%20were%20already%20knocking%20on%20the%20doors%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Altogether%20in%20the%20final%20hearing%20of%20the%20case%20there%20were%20five%20petitioners%20%E2%80%93%20apart%20from%20the%20lead%20petitioners%2C%20there%20were%20three%20tagged%20petitions%20representing%20the%20CPI(M)%2C%20Dr%20Jaya%20Thakur%20of%20the%20Congress%2C%20and%20banking%20lawyer%20Spandan%20Biswal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20mainstream%20media%20generally%20preferring%20to%20look%20the%20other%20way%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20could%20drive%20a%20truck%20through%20the%20objections%20raised%20by%20various%20authorities%20to%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme.%20The%20Reserve%20Bank%2C%20as%20the%20recent%20apex%20court%20judgment%20noted%2C%20had%20as%20early%20as%20January%202017%20written%20to%20the%20Finance%20Ministry%20objecting%20to%20the%20proposal%20which%20it%20argued%20militated%20against%20its%20own%20authority%20to%20issue%20bearer%20instruments.%20Later%20Urjit%20Patel%2C%20who%20was%20then%20governor%20of%20the%20apex%20bank%2C%20conveyed%20to%20the%20finance%20ministry%20his%20views%20on%20the%20risks%20of%20money%20laundering%2C%20forgery%20and%20cross%20border%20counterfeiting%20that%20could%20emanate%20from%20the%20issuance%20of%20the%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20also%20displayed%20some%20spine%20in%20those%20early%20days.%20The%20judgment%20observed%20that%20on%20May%2026%2C%202017%2C%20the%20ECI%20wrote%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Law%20%26amp%3B%20Justice%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20the%20amendments%20to%20the%20IT%20Act%2C%20RPA%2C%20and%20Companies%20Act%20introduced%20by%20the%20Finance%20Act%202017%2C%20will%20have%20a%20%E2%80%9Cserious%20impact%20on%20transparency%20of%20political%20finance%2Ffunding%20of%20political%20parties%E2%80%9D.%20The%20ECI%20also%20expressed%20concern%20over%20the%20negative%20impacts%20that%20removing%20the%20cap%20on%20corporate%20donations%20would%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20one%20by%20one%2C%20these%20institutions%20fell%20silent%2C%20with%20the%20Modi%20government%20displaying%20extraordinary%20gumption%20and%20persisting%20with%20the%20scheme.%20And%20why%20would%20it%20not%3F%20The%20electoral%20bonds%20arrangement%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20cornucopia%20that%20the%20late%20finance%20minister%2C%20Arun%20Jaitley%2C%20had%20bequeathed%20his%20party%2C%20which%20gave%20and%20gave.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20group%20that%20kept%20pushing%20back%20against%20it%20was%20the%20%E2%80%9CRTI-wallahs%E2%80%9D.%20It%20was%20their%20persistence%20which%20led%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20admitting%20in%20its%20order%20of%20April%2013%2C%202019%2C%20that%20the%20scheme%20gave%20rise%20to%20%E2%80%9Cweighty%20issues%20which%20have%20a%20bearing%20on%20the%20sanctity%20of%20the%20electoral%20process%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20bench%2C%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%2C%20refused%20to%20grant%20interim%20relief.%20A%20month%20later%2C%20in%20the%20general%20election%20that%20followed%2C%20the%20BJP%20emerged%20with%20an%20even%20bigger%20margin%20of%20votes%20than%20it%20had%20notched%20earlier%20(assisted%20undoubtedly%20by%20the%20generous%20flow%20of%20funds%20in%20its%20direction).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%20discouraging%20trajectory%2C%20the%20petitioners%20kept%20filing%20petitions%2C%20time%20and%20again%2C%20but%20to%20little%20avail.%20On%20occasion%20the%20petitioners%20even%20met%20with%20hostility%20from%20their%20lordships.%20When%20the%20petition%20came%20up%20before%20a%20bench%20led%20by%20then%20chief%20justice%2C%20S.A.%20Bobde%2C%20it%20was%20not%20only%20rejected%20but%20firmly%20rebuffed%20with%20the%20words%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20cannot%20be%20repeated%20applications%20seeking%20the%20same%20relief%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20days%20passed.%20In%20October%202023%2C%20with%20a%20new%20general%20election%20on%20the%20horizon%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20was%20once%20again%20approached%20by%20the%20petitioners.%20The%20bench%20led%20by%20the%20present%20chief%20justice%20saw%20the%20issue%20as%20one%20of%20%E2%80%9Cimportance%E2%80%9D%20and%20referred%20it%20to%20a%20constitution%20bench.%20A%20couple%20of%20hearings%20took%20place%20and%20a%20judgment%20was%20arrived%20at%20on%20November%202%2C%202023%2C%20which%20was%20reserved.%20The%20rest%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20is%20this%20back%20story%20important%20for%20journalists%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20all%20about%20information%2C%20the%20life%20force%20of%20the%20profession.%20Many%20serious%20journalists%20%E2%80%93%20not%20of%20course%20the%20bejewelled%20and%20suited%20types%20inhabiting%20prime%20time%20%E2%80%93%20realised%20its%20worth%20and%20the%20value%20of%20chasing%20this%20story.%20They%20went%20on%20to%20unearth%20the%20unique%20alphanumeric%20number%20on%20the%20bond%20certificates%3B%20access%20file%20notings%3B%20and%20keep%20a%20river%20of%20information%20flowing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20argument%20that%20the%20petitioners%20made%20to%20the%20court%20was%20straightforward%3A%20the%20opacity%20that%20marked%20the%20scheme%20%E2%80%9Cdefeats%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20know%20about%20the%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%20and%20promotes%20corruption.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Modi%20government%2C%20in%20its%20response%20was%20having%20none%20of%20that.%20It%20actually%20put%20forward%20the%20mind-blowing%20counter-argument%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccitizens%20did%20not%20have%20a%20%E2%80%98general%20right%20to%20know%20regarding%20the%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20emphasised%20that%20%E2%80%98right%20to%20know%E2%80%99%20itself%20is%20not%20a%20general%20right%20available%20to%20citizens%E2%80%9D%20(%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpart-of-secret-ballot-how-the-modi-govt-backed-electoral-bonds-in-the-supreme-court%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNew%2520Delhi%253A%2520The%2520Supreme%2520Court%2Canonymous%2520donations%2520to%2520political%2520parties.%5C%22%3EPart%20of%20Secret%20Ballot%E2%80%99%3A%20How%20the%20Modi%20Govt%20Backed%20Electoral%20Bonds%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20February%2016).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20arguments%20did%20not%20fortunately%20convince%20the%20bench.%20There%20was%20no%20getting%20away%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20%E2%80%9Canonymity%E2%80%9D%20was%20crucial%20to%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%2C%20yet%20this%20very%20non-disclosure%20of%20information%20on%20electoral%20contributions%20was%20clearly%20violative%20of%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20the%20voter%20and%20therefore%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%20guarantee%20in%20the%20constitution.%20This%20was%20the%20line%20the%20petitioners%20chose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%2C%20when%20it%20weighed%20in%2C%20cited%20two%20phases%20of%20court%20rulings%20on%20Article%2019%20(1)(a).%20The%20first%20linked%20the%20%E2%80%9Cright%20to%20information%20to%20the%20values%20of%20good%20governance%2C%20transparency%20and%20accountability%E2%80%9D%20and%20recognised%20the%20role%20of%20citizens%20in%20holding%20the%20state%20accountable%20for%20its%20actions%20and%20inactions%20and%20argued%20that%20they%20must%20possess%20relevant%20information%20in%20order%20to%20do%20this.%20In%20the%20second%20phase%2C%20the%20focus%20was%20on%20the%20evolution%20of%20the%20jurisprudence%20on%20the%20right%20to%20information.%20In%20the%20second%20phase%2C%20various%20rulings%20had%20recognised%20that%20%E2%80%9Ceffective%20participation%20in%20democratic%20governance%20is%20not%20just%20a%20means%20to%20an%20end%20but%20is%20an%20end%20in%20itself.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20how%20important%20to%20this%20process%20is%20information%20on%20political%20funding%3F%20The%20bench%20headed%20by%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20dwelt%20on%20this%20question%20and%20concluded%20that%20such%20information%20was%20essential%20if%20the%20voter%20is%20to%20exercise%20their%20franchise%20in%20an%20effective%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20they%20infringe%20upon%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20the%20voter%20by%20anonymizing%20contributions%20through%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20are%20violative%20of%20Article%2019%20(1)(a).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20power%20of%20information%20to%20animate%20democracy%20was%20the%20leitmotif%20of%20this%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImran%20Khan%20%E2%80%98virtually%E2%80%99%20won%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%2C%20or%20should%20we%20say%20Imran%20Khan%20and%20his%20Pakistan%20Tehreek-e-Insaf%20party%2C%20has%20beaten%20India%20in%20weaponising%20AI%20for%20electoral%20purposes%20%E2%80%93%20a%20trend%20that%20will%20almost%20certainly%20play%20out%20in%20the%20coming%20general%20election%20in%20this%20country%20later%20this%20year.%20But%20for%20Khan%20it%20was%20a%20case%20of%20necessity%20proving%20once%20again%20to%20be%20the%20mother%20of%20all%20invention.%20When%20he%20found%20himself%20in%20jail%2C%20for%20various%20alleged%20political%20crimes%20including%20fraud%20last%20August%2C%20he%20did%20not%20allow%20his%20incarceration%20to%20end%20his%20political%20ambitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20long%20an%20audio%20clip%20of%20his%20voice%20generated%20by%20AI%20addressed%20millions%20on%20social%20media%20in%20what%20was%20quickly%20labeled%20as%20a%20virtual%20election%20rally.%20The%20provenance%20of%20his%20speech%20had%20an%20interesting%20back%20story.%20It%20emerged%20from%20a%20script%20dictated%20by%20Khan%20in%20jail%20and%20a%20text-to-audio%20AI%20model%20was%20used%20to%20convert%20it%20into%20a%20speech%20which%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20drawn%20over%201.4%20million%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20just%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20frenetic%20period%20of%20campaigning%20for%20Khan%20%E2%80%93%20virtually.%20As%20the%20Pakistan%20general%20election%20drew%20closer%2C%20a%20four-minute%20declamation%20scripted%20in%20jail%2C%20vetted%20by%20lawyers%2C%20worked%20on%20by%20techies%20using%20an%20AI%20tool%20from%20ElevenLabs%2C%20went%20on%20to%20electrify%20the%20party%20base%20by%20mid-December.%20It%20was%20a%20hit%2C%20especially%20among%20the%20youngsters%20(Pakistan%20like%20India%20has%20a%20disproportionately%20higher%20number%20of%20young%20adults%20in%20its%20population%20of%20240%20million).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20time%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20audience%20on%20social%20media%20had%20quadrupled%20defeating%20the%20cynical%20stratagems%20of%20the%20Pakistan%20Army%20that%20went%20out%20of%20its%20way%20to%20bind%20the%20man%20and%20gag%20him%20%E2%80%93%20politically%20speaking.%20Apps%20were%20created%20so%20that%20the%20Voice%20could%20now%20seamlessly%20inhabit%20the%20Facebook%20and%20WhatsApp%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20counting%20day%20it%20was%20discovered%20that%20despite%20the%20man%20being%20in%20jail%2C%20the%20independents%20associated%20with%20his%20party%20had%20together%20got%20more%20votes%20than%20their%20counterparts%2C%20notching%20wins%20in%2097%20out%20of%20265%20seats.%20When%20his%20rivals%20claimed%20to%20have%20won%2C%20once%20again%20the%20AI%20version%20of%20Imran%20Khan%20emerged%2C%20this%20time%20with%20a%20victory%20speech%20complete%20with%20rhetorical%20embellishments%20characteristic%20of%20the%20original%3A%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9CMy%20beloved%20countrymen.%20By%20turning%20out%20in%20such%20huge%20numbers%20and%20exercising%20your%20democratic%20right%20of%20franchise%2C%20you%20have%20laid%20the%20foundation%20for%20the%20restoration%20of%20the%20freedom%20to%20exercise%20citizens%E2%80%99%20rights.%20I%20congratulate%20you%20all%20on%20helping%20us%20win%20the%20elections%20handsomely.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League-Nawaz%20(PML-N)%20and%20the%20Pakistan%20People%E2%80%99s%20party%20(PPP)%20cobbled%20up%20an%20understanding%20to%20form%20the%20next%20government%2C%20leaving%20Imran%20Khan%20by%20the%20wayside%20despite%20his%20%E2%80%9Cvictory%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20also%20means%20that%20the%20virtual%20Imran%20Khan%20will%20continue%20to%20rock%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20political%20boat%20in%20the%20years%20to%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVoices%20airbrushed%20out%20of%20the%20frame%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20lines%20jumped%20out%20of%20the%20page%20for%20me%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20families%20of%20those%20who%20had%20died%20on%2022%20December%20were%20not%20moved.%20Speaking%20about%20the%20new%20solar%20lights%20that%20had%20been%20set%20up%20across%20the%20village%20under%20Operation%20Sadbhavana%2C%20Lal%E2%80%99s%20daughter-in-law%2C%20Rangeela%20Begum%2C%20told%20me%2C%20%E2%80%98They%20blacked%20out%20our%20lives%20and%20are%20now%20installing%20solar%20lights%E2%80%A6this%20is%20no%20substitute%20for%20justice.%20It%E2%80%99s%20just%20hooliganism.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20affected%20families%2C%20the%20bundles%20of%20cash%20they%20received%E2%80%94Rs%2010%20lakh%20for%20the%20dead%20and%20lesser%20for%20the%20injured%E2%80%94were%20expected%20to%20replace%20their%20loved%20ones.%20Nazir%2C%20Shaukat%E2%80%99s%20father%2C%20was%20visited%20by%20the%20commanding%20officer%20of%20the%2016%20RR%20and%20a%20brigadier%2C%20who%20handed%20him%20Rs%2010%20lakh.%20Vali%20was%20given%20the%20same%20amount.%20He%20told%20me%20he%20did%20not%20know%20what%20to%20do%20with%20it.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20labourers%20and%20I%20have%20worked%20my%20whole%20life%20with%20the%20border%20roads%20organisation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CI%20raised%20my%20children%20in%20extreme%20poverty%20and%20hoped%20one%20day%20they%20will%20take%20care%20of%20me%20when%20I%20get%20old.%E2%80%9D%20The%20money%20would%20do%20little%20to%20help.%20Farooq%20got%20Rs%202.3%20lakh%2C%20while%20Irfaan%20got%20Rs%201.5%20lakh.%20Fazal%20was%20given%20Rs%202.5%20lakh.%20Now%20barely%20able%20to%20walk%2C%20he%20told%20me%20the%20money%20was%20meaningless.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20five%20kids%20and%20a%20family%20of%20seven%20to%20support.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20see%20myself%20being%20able%20to%20work%20ever%20again.%E2%80%9D%20(%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fread-the-caravans-article-on-army-torture-the-union-government-wants-taken-down%5C%22%3EThe%20Caravan%E2%80%99s%20Article%20on%20Army%20Torture%20the%20Union%20Government%20Wants%20Taken%20Down%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20February%2013)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVanessa%20Dougnac%20is%20deported%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20shameful%20that%20former%20South%20Asia%20Correspondent%20for%20%3Cem%3ELa%20Croix%2C%20Le%20Point%2C%20Le%20Temps%2C%20Le%20Soir%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20who%20has%20lived%20and%20worked%20as%20a%20professional%20in%20India%20for%20over%20two%20decades%2C%20has%20been%20deported%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20for%20her%20independent%20reporting%20on%20the%20affairs%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20many%20in%20the%20Indian%20journalistic%20community%20who%20found%20this%20act%20of%20deportation%20abhorrent%20and%20a%20violation%20of%20media%20freedom%20in%20a%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20farewell%20letter%20was%20widely%20covered%20in%20the%20print%20media%2C%20along%20with%20its%20resonating%20opening%20lines%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20writing%20these%20words%20in%20tears.%20Today%2C%20I%20am%20leaving%20India%2C%20the%20country%20where%20I%20came%2025%20years%20ago%20as%20a%20student%2C%20and%20where%20I%20have%20worked%20for%2023%20years%20as%20a%20journalist.%20The%20place%20where%20I%20married%2C%20raised%20my%20son%2C%20and%20which%20I%20call%20my%20home.%C2%A0Leaving%20is%20not%20my%20choice%E2%80%9D%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Ffrench-journalist-vanessa-dougnac-leaves-india-amid-expulsion-threat%5C%22%3EFrench%20Journalist%20Vanessa%20Dougnac%20Leaves%20India%20Amid%20Expulsion%20Threat%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20February%2016).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReaders%20write%20in%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMedia%20repression%20and%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protests%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESujata%20Madhok%20and%20A.M.%20Jigeesh%2C%20president%20and%20general%20secretary%20respectively%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Union%20of%20Journalists%2C%20wrote%20in%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Delhi%20Union%20of%20Journalists%20(DUJ)%20is%20deeply%20concerned%20that%20journalists%20are%20among%20those%20injured%20by%20police%20action%20during%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protests.%20Two%20journalists%2C%20Satender%20Chauhan%20and%20Niel%20Bhalinder%20Singh%2C%20suffered%20injuries%20while%20covering%20the%20protests%20at%20the%20Shambhu%20border%20yesterday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSatender%20Chauhan%2C%20correspondent%20for%20Aaj%20Tak%2C%20was%20%E2%80%98live%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20channel%20when%20he%20was%20hit%20by%20a%20%E2%80%98chharra%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20eye%20area.%20The%20channel%20showed%20a%20colleague%20helping%20him%20to%20leave%20the%20spot.%20He%20was%20taken%20to%20hospital.%20Niel%20Bhalinder%20Singh%20of%20the%20Savera%20group%20of%20newspapers%20was%20taken%20to%20hospital%20bleeding%20heavily%20as%20a%20tear%20gas%20shell%20fired%20by%20a%20drone%20fell%20on%20his%20head.%20Unconfirmed%20reports%20have%20also%20come%20in%20regarding%20injuries%20to%20other%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Patiala%20Media%20Club%20and%20the%20Chandigarh%20Press%20Club%20have%20demanded%20safety%20for%20journalists%20covering%20such%20events.%20The%20DUJ%20is%20also%20concerned%20at%20the%20Internet%20shutdown%20imposed%20in%20seven%20districts%20of%20Haryana%20and%20three%20districts%20of%20Rajasthan%20which%20has%20made%20it%20extremely%20difficult%20for%20journalists%20to%20cover%20the%20protests.%20They%20also%20note%20that%20social%20media%20accounts%20of%20some%20journalists%20including%20Mandeep%20Punia%20of%20Gaon%20Savera%20have%20been%20taken%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDUJ%20condemned%20the%20violence%20on%20protesting%20farmers%20that%20has%20led%20to%20injuries%20and%20hospitalizations.%20They%20urged%20the%20central%20government%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20demands%20are%20settled%20amicably.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20response%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReporting%20on%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20agitation%20has%20always%20been%20fraught.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20eight%20journalists%20who%20had%20reported%20on%20the%20violence%20that%20broke%20out%20on%20Republic%20Day%20in%20Delhi%2C%20including%20the%20founder-editor%20of%20The%20Wire%2C%20had%20sedition%20and%20other%20criminal%20charges%20brought%20against%20them.%20This%20time%2C%20a%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20piece%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ffarmers-social-media-accounts-withheld-protest%5C%22%3EAgenda%20Is%20to%20Silence%20Us%E2%80%99%3A%20Key%20Social%20Media%20Accounts%20Withheld%2C%20Farmers%20Vow%20to%20Boycott%20Centre%E2%80%99s%20Meetings%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20(February%2014)%2C%20has%20highlighted%20how%20X%20accounts%20and%20Facebook%20pages%20of%20prominent%20farmer%20leaders%20as%20well%20as%20many%20others%20have%20been%20withheld.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20also%20banned%20official%20pages%20which%20supported%20the%20movement%20and%20posted%20updates%20on%20it%2C%20like%20%40Tractor2twitr_P%20run%20by%20Bhavjit%20Singh%2C%20Bhartiya%20Kisan%20Union%20(Shaheed%20Bhagat%20Singh)%20and%20Progressive%20Farmers%20Front%2C%20run%20by%20Guramneet%20Singh%20Mangat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20more%2C%20the%20process%20of%20withholding%20these%20accounts%20has%20been%20largely%20understood%20to%20be%20opaque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20very%20interesting%20aspect%20of%20this%20repression%20was%20highlighted%20by%20Bhavjit%20Singh%2C%20who%20is%20associated%20with%20the%20%40Tractor2Twitr_i%20page%20on%20X.%20In%20a%20conversation%20with%20the%20Wire%20which%20was%20quoted%20in%20the%20story%2C%20he%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20accounts%20were%20withheld%20even%20as%20farmer%20leaders%20were%20sitting%20at%20a%20meeting%20with%20union%20ministers%20on%20February%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20an%20assumption%20that%20it%20is%20not%20just%20the%20Union%20government%20but%20the%20Punjab%20government%20too%20which%20was%20involved%20in%20singling%20out%20farmer%20union%20leaders%E2%80%99%20accounts.%20This%20is%20a%20dangerous%20trend%2C%20as%20those%20accounts%20which%20were%20running%20propaganda%20against%20farmers%20are%20getting%20support%20while%20the%20official%20mouthpieces%20of%20farmers%20meant%20to%20debunk%20the%20propaganda%20and%20misinformation%20are%20being%20targeted.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWrite%20to%20ombudsperson%40thewire.in.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708167903000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F10%2F30183824%2FIMG_4397-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fbackstory-electoral-bond-journalists-ai-imran-khan-farmers%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20fortnightly%20column%20from%20The%20Wire's%20ombudsperson.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fbackstory-electoral-bond-journalists-ai-imran-khan-farmers%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Backstory%20%7C%20Moral%20of%20the%20Electoral%20Bond%20Story%3A%20Information%20Is%20Essential%20for%20Democracy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F10%2F30183824%2FIMG_4397-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3ETurning%20points%20have%20come%20but%20rarely%20in%20the%20ten%20years%20of%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%2C%20given%20its%20astounding%20success%20in%20maintaining%20an%20iron-clad%2C%20surveillance-driven%20grip%20on%20every%20institution%20in%20the%20country.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20verdict%20of%20February%2015%20that%20outlawed%20electoral%20bonds%20is%20emphatically%20one%20of%20them%2C%20and%20needs%20to%20be%20recognised%20as%20another%20chance%20that%20has%20been%20given%20to%20us%2C%20as%20Indians%2C%20to%20redeem%20our%20besmirched%20republic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20moment%20stands%20as%20testimony%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20capacity%20to%20assert%20itself%2C%20something%20we%20felt%20it%20had%20become%20incapable%20of%20doing.%C2%A0%20It%20remembered%20its%20obligations%20to%20the%20Constitution%20and%20to%20one%20of%20its%20foundational%20principles%20%E2%80%93%20Article%2019%201(a)%20guaranteeing%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20expression%20as%20well%20as%20the%20concomitant%20right%20to%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20question%20is%2C%20would%20the%20court%20have%20done%20the%20right%20thing%20and%20outlawed%20electoral%20bonds%20if%20it%20had%20not%20been%20for%20the%20dogged%20resistance%20of%20an%20unsung%2C%20often%20attacked%20and%20abused%20tribe%2C%20sometimes%20derided%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9CRTI-%3Cem%3Ewallahs%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%3F%20It%20is%20these%20women%20and%20men%20who%20kept%20up%20their%20date%20with%20the%20courts%2C%20%3Cem%3Etarikh-pe-tarikh%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20along%20with%20their%20praetorian%20guard%20of%20constitutional%20lawyers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20journalist%20Nitin%20Sethi%2C%20tweeted%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20wasn%E2%80%99t%201%20or%202%20people%20or%20organisations.%20Many%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSauravDassss%5C%22%3E%40SauravDas%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20the%20Common%20Cause%2C%20Anjali%20B%20and%20her%20colleagues%2C%20Venkatesh%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmediatrack_in%5C%22%3E%40mediatrack%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fpoonamjourno%5C%22%3E%40poonamjourno%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAmannama%5C%22%3E%40Amannama%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FSharanyaHK%5C%22%3E%40SharanyaHK%3C%2Fa%3E.%20With%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FCommodoreBatra%5C%22%3E%40CommodoreBatra%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26amp%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fadrspeaks%5C%22%3E%40adrspeaks%3C%2Fa%3E%20leading.%20It%20took%20a%20village.%20But%20it%20ain%E2%80%99t%20over%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20did%20this%20right%20from%20the%20days%20when%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%20was%20introduced%20as%20part%20of%20the%20Finance%20Bill%20in%20the%20Budget%20of%20February%202017.%20Within%20a%20span%20of%20six%20months%2C%20the%20lead%20petitioners%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20and%20Common%20Cause%2C%20were%20already%20knocking%20on%20the%20doors%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Altogether%20in%20the%20final%20hearing%20of%20the%20case%20there%20were%20five%20petitioners%20%E2%80%93%20apart%20from%20the%20lead%20petitioners%2C%20there%20were%20three%20tagged%20petitions%20representing%20the%20CPI(M)%2C%20Dr%20Jaya%20Thakur%20of%20the%20Congress%2C%20and%20banking%20lawyer%20Spandan%20Biswal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20mainstream%20media%20generally%20preferring%20to%20look%20the%20other%20way%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20could%20drive%20a%20truck%20through%20the%20objections%20raised%20by%20various%20authorities%20to%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme.%20The%20Reserve%20Bank%2C%20as%20the%20recent%20apex%20court%20judgment%20noted%2C%20had%20as%20early%20as%20January%202017%20written%20to%20the%20Finance%20Ministry%20objecting%20to%20the%20proposal%20which%20it%20argued%20militated%20against%20its%20own%20authority%20to%20issue%20bearer%20instruments.%20Later%20Urjit%20Patel%2C%20who%20was%20then%20governor%20of%20the%20apex%20bank%2C%20conveyed%20to%20the%20finance%20ministry%20his%20views%20on%20the%20risks%20of%20money%20laundering%2C%20forgery%20and%20cross%20border%20counterfeiting%20that%20could%20emanate%20from%20the%20issuance%20of%20the%20bonds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20also%20displayed%20some%20spine%20in%20those%20early%20days.%20The%20judgment%20observed%20that%20on%20May%2026%2C%202017%2C%20the%20ECI%20wrote%20to%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Law%20%26amp%3B%20Justice%2C%20pointing%20out%20that%20the%20amendments%20to%20the%20IT%20Act%2C%20RPA%2C%20and%20Companies%20Act%20introduced%20by%20the%20Finance%20Act%202017%2C%20will%20have%20a%20%E2%80%9Cserious%20impact%20on%20transparency%20of%20political%20finance%2Ffunding%20of%20political%20parties%E2%80%9D.%20The%20ECI%20also%20expressed%20concern%20over%20the%20negative%20impacts%20that%20removing%20the%20cap%20on%20corporate%20donations%20would%20have.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20one%20by%20one%2C%20these%20institutions%20fell%20silent%2C%20with%20the%20Modi%20government%20displaying%20extraordinary%20gumption%20and%20persisting%20with%20the%20scheme.%20And%20why%20would%20it%20not%3F%20The%20electoral%20bonds%20arrangement%20proved%20to%20be%20a%20cornucopia%20that%20the%20late%20finance%20minister%2C%20Arun%20Jaitley%2C%20had%20bequeathed%20his%20party%2C%20which%20gave%20and%20gave.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20group%20that%20kept%20pushing%20back%20against%20it%20was%20the%20%E2%80%9CRTI-wallahs%E2%80%9D.%20It%20was%20their%20persistence%20which%20led%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20admitting%20in%20its%20order%20of%20April%2013%2C%202019%2C%20that%20the%20scheme%20gave%20rise%20to%20%E2%80%9Cweighty%20issues%20which%20have%20a%20bearing%20on%20the%20sanctity%20of%20the%20electoral%20process%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20that%20bench%2C%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20Ranjan%20Gogoi%2C%20refused%20to%20grant%20interim%20relief.%20A%20month%20later%2C%20in%20the%20general%20election%20that%20followed%2C%20the%20BJP%20emerged%20with%20an%20even%20bigger%20margin%20of%20votes%20than%20it%20had%20notched%20earlier%20(assisted%20undoubtedly%20by%20the%20generous%20flow%20of%20funds%20in%20its%20direction).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%20discouraging%20trajectory%2C%20the%20petitioners%20kept%20filing%20petitions%2C%20time%20and%20again%2C%20but%20to%20little%20avail.%20On%20occasion%20the%20petitioners%20even%20met%20with%20hostility%20from%20their%20lordships.%20When%20the%20petition%20came%20up%20before%20a%20bench%20led%20by%20then%20chief%20justice%2C%20S.A.%20Bobde%2C%20it%20was%20not%20only%20rejected%20but%20firmly%20rebuffed%20with%20the%20words%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthere%20cannot%20be%20repeated%20applications%20seeking%20the%20same%20relief%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20days%20passed.%20In%20October%202023%2C%20with%20a%20new%20general%20election%20on%20the%20horizon%2C%20the%20apex%20court%20was%20once%20again%20approached%20by%20the%20petitioners.%20The%20bench%20led%20by%20the%20present%20chief%20justice%20saw%20the%20issue%20as%20one%20of%20%E2%80%9Cimportance%E2%80%9D%20and%20referred%20it%20to%20a%20constitution%20bench.%20A%20couple%20of%20hearings%20took%20place%20and%20a%20judgment%20was%20arrived%20at%20on%20November%202%2C%202023%2C%20which%20was%20reserved.%20The%20rest%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20is%20this%20back%20story%20important%20for%20journalists%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20all%20about%20information%2C%20the%20life%20force%20of%20the%20profession.%20Many%20serious%20journalists%20%E2%80%93%20not%20of%20course%20the%20bejewelled%20and%20suited%20types%20inhabiting%20prime%20time%20%E2%80%93%20realised%20its%20worth%20and%20the%20value%20of%20chasing%20this%20story.%20They%20went%20on%20to%20unearth%20the%20unique%20alphanumeric%20number%20on%20the%20bond%20certificates%3B%20access%20file%20notings%3B%20and%20keep%20a%20river%20of%20information%20flowing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20argument%20that%20the%20petitioners%20made%20to%20the%20court%20was%20straightforward%3A%20the%20opacity%20that%20marked%20the%20scheme%20%E2%80%9Cdefeats%20the%20people%E2%80%99s%20right%20to%20know%20about%20the%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%20and%20promotes%20corruption.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Modi%20government%2C%20in%20its%20response%20was%20having%20none%20of%20that.%20It%20actually%20put%20forward%20the%20mind-blowing%20counter-argument%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccitizens%20did%20not%20have%20a%20%E2%80%98general%20right%20to%20know%20regarding%20the%20funding%20of%20political%20parties%E2%80%99%2C%20and%20emphasised%20that%20%E2%80%98right%20to%20know%E2%80%99%20itself%20is%20not%20a%20general%20right%20available%20to%20citizens%E2%80%9D%20(%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fpart-of-secret-ballot-how-the-modi-govt-backed-electoral-bonds-in-the-supreme-court%23%3A~%3Atext%3DNew%2520Delhi%253A%2520The%2520Supreme%2520Court%2Canonymous%2520donations%2520to%2520political%2520parties.%5C%22%3EPart%20of%20Secret%20Ballot%E2%80%99%3A%20How%20the%20Modi%20Govt%20Backed%20Electoral%20Bonds%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20February%2016).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESuch%20arguments%20did%20not%20fortunately%20convince%20the%20bench.%20There%20was%20no%20getting%20away%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20%E2%80%9Canonymity%E2%80%9D%20was%20crucial%20to%20the%20electoral%20bond%20scheme%2C%20yet%20this%20very%20non-disclosure%20of%20information%20on%20electoral%20contributions%20was%20clearly%20violative%20of%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20the%20voter%20and%20therefore%20the%20freedom%20of%20expression%20guarantee%20in%20the%20constitution.%20This%20was%20the%20line%20the%20petitioners%20chose.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%2C%20when%20it%20weighed%20in%2C%20cited%20two%20phases%20of%20court%20rulings%20on%20Article%2019%20(1)(a).%20The%20first%20linked%20the%20%E2%80%9Cright%20to%20information%20to%20the%20values%20of%20good%20governance%2C%20transparency%20and%20accountability%E2%80%9D%20and%20recognised%20the%20role%20of%20citizens%20in%20holding%20the%20state%20accountable%20for%20its%20actions%20and%20inactions%20and%20argued%20that%20they%20must%20possess%20relevant%20information%20in%20order%20to%20do%20this.%20In%20the%20second%20phase%2C%20the%20focus%20was%20on%20the%20evolution%20of%20the%20jurisprudence%20on%20the%20right%20to%20information.%20In%20the%20second%20phase%2C%20various%20rulings%20had%20recognised%20that%20%E2%80%9Ceffective%20participation%20in%20democratic%20governance%20is%20not%20just%20a%20means%20to%20an%20end%20but%20is%20an%20end%20in%20itself.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20how%20important%20to%20this%20process%20is%20information%20on%20political%20funding%3F%20The%20bench%20headed%20by%20CJI%20Chandrachud%20dwelt%20on%20this%20question%20and%20concluded%20that%20such%20information%20was%20essential%20if%20the%20voter%20is%20to%20exercise%20their%20franchise%20in%20an%20effective%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETherefore%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Electoral%20Bond%20Scheme%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20they%20infringe%20upon%20the%20right%20to%20information%20of%20the%20voter%20by%20anonymizing%20contributions%20through%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20are%20violative%20of%20Article%2019%20(1)(a).%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20power%20of%20information%20to%20animate%20democracy%20was%20the%20leitmotif%20of%20this%20judgment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImran%20Khan%20%E2%80%98virtually%E2%80%99%20won%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPakistan%2C%20or%20should%20we%20say%20Imran%20Khan%20and%20his%20Pakistan%20Tehreek-e-Insaf%20party%2C%20has%20beaten%20India%20in%20weaponising%20AI%20for%20electoral%20purposes%20%E2%80%93%20a%20trend%20that%20will%20almost%20certainly%20play%20out%20in%20the%20coming%20general%20election%20in%20this%20country%20later%20this%20year.%20But%20for%20Khan%20it%20was%20a%20case%20of%20necessity%20proving%20once%20again%20to%20be%20the%20mother%20of%20all%20invention.%20When%20he%20found%20himself%20in%20jail%2C%20for%20various%20alleged%20political%20crimes%20including%20fraud%20last%20August%2C%20he%20did%20not%20allow%20his%20incarceration%20to%20end%20his%20political%20ambitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20long%20an%20audio%20clip%20of%20his%20voice%20generated%20by%20AI%20addressed%20millions%20on%20social%20media%20in%20what%20was%20quickly%20labeled%20as%20a%20virtual%20election%20rally.%20The%20provenance%20of%20his%20speech%20had%20an%20interesting%20back%20story.%20It%20emerged%20from%20a%20script%20dictated%20by%20Khan%20in%20jail%20and%20a%20text-to-audio%20AI%20model%20was%20used%20to%20convert%20it%20into%20a%20speech%20which%20is%20believed%20to%20have%20drawn%20over%201.4%20million%20views.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20just%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20frenetic%20period%20of%20campaigning%20for%20Khan%20%E2%80%93%20virtually.%20As%20the%20Pakistan%20general%20election%20drew%20closer%2C%20a%20four-minute%20declamation%20scripted%20in%20jail%2C%20vetted%20by%20lawyers%2C%20worked%20on%20by%20techies%20using%20an%20AI%20tool%20from%20ElevenLabs%2C%20went%20on%20to%20electrify%20the%20party%20base%20by%20mid-December.%20It%20was%20a%20hit%2C%20especially%20among%20the%20youngsters%20(Pakistan%20like%20India%20has%20a%20disproportionately%20higher%20number%20of%20young%20adults%20in%20its%20population%20of%20240%20million).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20time%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20audience%20on%20social%20media%20had%20quadrupled%20defeating%20the%20cynical%20stratagems%20of%20the%20Pakistan%20Army%20that%20went%20out%20of%20its%20way%20to%20bind%20the%20man%20and%20gag%20him%20%E2%80%93%20politically%20speaking.%20Apps%20were%20created%20so%20that%20the%20Voice%20could%20now%20seamlessly%20inhabit%20the%20Facebook%20and%20WhatsApp%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20counting%20day%20it%20was%20discovered%20that%20despite%20the%20man%20being%20in%20jail%2C%20the%20independents%20associated%20with%20his%20party%20had%20together%20got%20more%20votes%20than%20their%20counterparts%2C%20notching%20wins%20in%2097%20out%20of%20265%20seats.%20When%20his%20rivals%20claimed%20to%20have%20won%2C%20once%20again%20the%20AI%20version%20of%20Imran%20Khan%20emerged%2C%20this%20time%20with%20a%20victory%20speech%20complete%20with%20rhetorical%20embellishments%20characteristic%20of%20the%20original%3A%C2%A0%20%E2%80%9CMy%20beloved%20countrymen.%20By%20turning%20out%20in%20such%20huge%20numbers%20and%20exercising%20your%20democratic%20right%20of%20franchise%2C%20you%20have%20laid%20the%20foundation%20for%20the%20restoration%20of%20the%20freedom%20to%20exercise%20citizens%E2%80%99%20rights.%20I%20congratulate%20you%20all%20on%20helping%20us%20win%20the%20elections%20handsomely.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20Pakistan%20Muslim%20League-Nawaz%20(PML-N)%20and%20the%20Pakistan%20People%E2%80%99s%20party%20(PPP)%20cobbled%20up%20an%20understanding%20to%20form%20the%20next%20government%2C%20leaving%20Imran%20Khan%20by%20the%20wayside%20despite%20his%20%E2%80%9Cvictory%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20also%20means%20that%20the%20virtual%20Imran%20Khan%20will%20continue%20to%20rock%20Pakistan%E2%80%99s%20political%20boat%20in%20the%20years%20to%20follow.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVoices%20airbrushed%20out%20of%20the%20frame%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20lines%20jumped%20out%20of%20the%20page%20for%20me%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20families%20of%20those%20who%20had%20died%20on%2022%20December%20were%20not%20moved.%20Speaking%20about%20the%20new%20solar%20lights%20that%20had%20been%20set%20up%20across%20the%20village%20under%20Operation%20Sadbhavana%2C%20Lal%E2%80%99s%20daughter-in-law%2C%20Rangeela%20Begum%2C%20told%20me%2C%20%E2%80%98They%20blacked%20out%20our%20lives%20and%20are%20now%20installing%20solar%20lights%E2%80%A6this%20is%20no%20substitute%20for%20justice.%20It%E2%80%99s%20just%20hooliganism.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFor%20the%20affected%20families%2C%20the%20bundles%20of%20cash%20they%20received%E2%80%94Rs%2010%20lakh%20for%20the%20dead%20and%20lesser%20for%20the%20injured%E2%80%94were%20expected%20to%20replace%20their%20loved%20ones.%20Nazir%2C%20Shaukat%E2%80%99s%20father%2C%20was%20visited%20by%20the%20commanding%20officer%20of%20the%2016%20RR%20and%20a%20brigadier%2C%20who%20handed%20him%20Rs%2010%20lakh.%20Vali%20was%20given%20the%20same%20amount.%20He%20told%20me%20he%20did%20not%20know%20what%20to%20do%20with%20it.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20labourers%20and%20I%20have%20worked%20my%20whole%20life%20with%20the%20border%20roads%20organisation%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%20%E2%80%9CI%20raised%20my%20children%20in%20extreme%20poverty%20and%20hoped%20one%20day%20they%20will%20take%20care%20of%20me%20when%20I%20get%20old.%E2%80%9D%20The%20money%20would%20do%20little%20to%20help.%20Farooq%20got%20Rs%202.3%20lakh%2C%20while%20Irfaan%20got%20Rs%201.5%20lakh.%20Fazal%20was%20given%20Rs%202.5%20lakh.%20Now%20barely%20able%20to%20walk%2C%20he%20told%20me%20the%20money%20was%20meaningless.%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20five%20kids%20and%20a%20family%20of%20seven%20to%20support.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20see%20myself%20being%20able%20to%20work%20ever%20again.%E2%80%9D%20(%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fread-the-caravans-article-on-army-torture-the-union-government-wants-taken-down%5C%22%3EThe%20Caravan%E2%80%99s%20Article%20on%20Army%20Torture%20the%20Union%20Government%20Wants%20Taken%20Down%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20February%2013)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EVanessa%20Dougnac%20is%20deported%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20shameful%20that%20former%20South%20Asia%20Correspondent%20for%20%3Cem%3ELa%20Croix%2C%20Le%20Point%2C%20Le%20Temps%2C%20Le%20Soir%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20who%20has%20lived%20and%20worked%20as%20a%20professional%20in%20India%20for%20over%20two%20decades%2C%20has%20been%20deported%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20for%20her%20independent%20reporting%20on%20the%20affairs%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20many%20in%20the%20Indian%20journalistic%20community%20who%20found%20this%20act%20of%20deportation%20abhorrent%20and%20a%20violation%20of%20media%20freedom%20in%20a%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20farewell%20letter%20was%20widely%20covered%20in%20the%20print%20media%2C%20along%20with%20its%20resonating%20opening%20lines%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%20writing%20these%20words%20in%20tears.%20Today%2C%20I%20am%20leaving%20India%2C%20the%20country%20where%20I%20came%2025%20years%20ago%20as%20a%20student%2C%20and%20where%20I%20have%20worked%20for%2023%20years%20as%20a%20journalist.%20The%20place%20where%20I%20married%2C%20raised%20my%20son%2C%20and%20which%20I%20call%20my%20home.%C2%A0Leaving%20is%20not%20my%20choice%E2%80%9D%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Ffrench-journalist-vanessa-dougnac-leaves-india-amid-expulsion-threat%5C%22%3EFrench%20Journalist%20Vanessa%20Dougnac%20Leaves%20India%20Amid%20Expulsion%20Threat%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20February%2016).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EReaders%20write%20in%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMedia%20repression%20and%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protests%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESujata%20Madhok%20and%20A.M.%20Jigeesh%2C%20president%20and%20general%20secretary%20respectively%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Union%20of%20Journalists%2C%20wrote%20in%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Delhi%20Union%20of%20Journalists%20(DUJ)%20is%20deeply%20concerned%20that%20journalists%20are%20among%20those%20injured%20by%20police%20action%20during%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protests.%20Two%20journalists%2C%20Satender%20Chauhan%20and%20Niel%20Bhalinder%20Singh%2C%20suffered%20injuries%20while%20covering%20the%20protests%20at%20the%20Shambhu%20border%20yesterday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSatender%20Chauhan%2C%20correspondent%20for%20Aaj%20Tak%2C%20was%20%E2%80%98live%E2%80%99%20on%20the%20channel%20when%20he%20was%20hit%20by%20a%20%E2%80%98chharra%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20eye%20area.%20The%20channel%20showed%20a%20colleague%20helping%20him%20to%20leave%20the%20spot.%20He%20was%20taken%20to%20hospital.%20Niel%20Bhalinder%20Singh%20of%20the%20Savera%20group%20of%20newspapers%20was%20taken%20to%20hospital%20bleeding%20heavily%20as%20a%20tear%20gas%20shell%20fired%20by%20a%20drone%20fell%20on%20his%20head.%20Unconfirmed%20reports%20have%20also%20come%20in%20regarding%20injuries%20to%20other%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20Patiala%20Media%20Club%20and%20the%20Chandigarh%20Press%20Club%20have%20demanded%20safety%20for%20journalists%20covering%20such%20events.%20The%20DUJ%20is%20also%20concerned%20at%20the%20Internet%20shutdown%20imposed%20in%20seven%20districts%20of%20Haryana%20and%20three%20districts%20of%20Rajasthan%20which%20has%20made%20it%20extremely%20difficult%20for%20journalists%20to%20cover%20the%20protests.%20They%20also%20note%20that%20social%20media%20accounts%20of%20some%20journalists%20including%20Mandeep%20Punia%20of%20Gaon%20Savera%20have%20been%20taken%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDUJ%20condemned%20the%20violence%20on%20protesting%20farmers%20that%20has%20led%20to%20injuries%20and%20hospitalizations.%20They%20urged%20the%20central%20government%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20demands%20are%20settled%20amicably.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMy%20response%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReporting%20on%20the%20farmers%E2%80%99%20agitation%20has%20always%20been%20fraught.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20eight%20journalists%20who%20had%20reported%20on%20the%20violence%20that%20broke%20out%20on%20Republic%20Day%20in%20Delhi%2C%20including%20the%20founder-editor%20of%20The%20Wire%2C%20had%20sedition%20and%20other%20criminal%20charges%20brought%20against%20them.%20This%20time%2C%20a%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20piece%2C%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Ffarmers-social-media-accounts-withheld-protest%5C%22%3EAgenda%20Is%20to%20Silence%20Us%E2%80%99%3A%20Key%20Social%20Media%20Accounts%20Withheld%2C%20Farmers%20Vow%20to%20Boycott%20Centre%E2%80%99s%20Meetings%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%99%20(February%2014)%2C%20has%20highlighted%20how%20X%20accounts%20and%20Facebook%20pages%20of%20prominent%20farmer%20leaders%20as%20well%20as%20many%20others%20have%20been%20withheld.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20also%20banned%20official%20pages%20which%20supported%20the%20movement%20and%20posted%20updates%20on%20it%2C%20like%20%40Tractor2twitr_P%20run%20by%20Bhavjit%20Singh%2C%20Bhartiya%20Kisan%20Union%20(Shaheed%20Bhagat%20Singh)%20and%20Progressive%20Farmers%20Front%2C%20run%20by%20Guramneet%20Singh%20Mangat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20more%2C%20the%20process%20of%20withholding%20these%20accounts%20has%20been%20largely%20understood%20to%20be%20opaque.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20very%20interesting%20aspect%20of%20this%20repression%20was%20highlighted%20by%20Bhavjit%20Singh%2C%20who%20is%20associated%20with%20the%20%40Tractor2Twitr_i%20page%20on%20X.%20In%20a%20conversation%20with%20the%20Wire%20which%20was%20quoted%20in%20the%20story%2C%20he%20pointed%20out%20that%20the%20accounts%20were%20withheld%20even%20as%20farmer%20leaders%20were%20sitting%20at%20a%20meeting%20with%20union%20ministers%20on%20February%2012.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20an%20assumption%20that%20it%20is%20not%20just%20the%20Union%20government%20but%20the%20Punjab%20government%20too%20which%20was%20involved%20in%20singling%20out%20farmer%20union%20leaders%E2%80%99%20accounts.%20This%20is%20a%20dangerous%20trend%2C%20as%20those%20accounts%20which%20were%20running%20propaganda%20against%20farmers%20are%20getting%20support%20while%20the%20official%20mouthpieces%20of%20farmers%20meant%20to%20debunk%20the%20propaganda%20and%20misinformation%20are%20being%20targeted.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EWrite%20to%20ombudsperson%40thewire.in.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1708167903000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F10%2F30183824%2FIMG_4397-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fbackstory-electoral-bond-journalists-ai-imran-khan-farmers%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20fortnightly%20column%20from%20The%20Wire's%20ombudsperson.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fbacksto